title: thin batter for deep frying
directions: Prepare food to be fried.
Dry food before dipping in batter. Heat fat or oil to 375°.
Beat ingredients for batter until smooth.
Coat prepared food with flour.
With tongs or fork, dip food into batter, allowing excess batter to drop into bowl.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Soften cheese.
Mix all ingredients on low speed.

title: christmas punch
directions: Makes approximately 75 cups.

title: crazy lemon cake
directions: Beat for 2 minutes, lemon gelatin, 3/4 cup cold water and 4 eggs.
Add and beat for 1 minute, lemon cake mix and vegetable oil. Bake in 9 x 11-inch Pyrex cake pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from the oven and after a couple of minutes, prick with a large fork and spoon the following over:
sugar and lemon juice.

title: delicious shrimp dinner
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Mix until smooth, stirring constantly.
Add Pet milk, and cook over medium heat, until sauce is thickened.
Add Cheddar and Parmesan cheeses.
Stir until melted.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Stir together the chocolate, marshmallows and milk; melt in microwave.
Mix with the vanilla and Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour mixture over; sprinkle with slivered almonds.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush entire box of Oreos (your "dirt") in blender or food processor.
Combine softened cream cheese and softened butter with confectioners sugar.
Mix pudding with milk until it thickens. Fold cream cheese mixture into pudding and add whipped topping. Put 1/3 "dirt" into an 8-inch flower pot (you may have to cover holes in bottom of pot first).
Mix 1/3 "dirt" with pudding mixture and pour into pot.
Place 4 gummy worms into mixture.
Spread remaining 1/3 dirt on top and place 2 worms into mixture, leaving their heads showing.
Place silk flowers into pot.
Place pot in middle of table as centerpiece and convince your guests that is is okay to eat the centerpiece.

title: corn scallop casserole
directions: Mix corn, onion and green pepper.
Place half of mixture in bottom of 1-quart buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle half of crumbs over the corn.
Add rest of corn mixture and rest of cracker crumbs.
Mix salt, pepper and milk; pour over corn.
Dab butter on the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Beat egg with mayonnaise, sugar and pimentos. Stir in chopped onion and bell pepper, then pour the mixture over the squash.
Cover; bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Uncover; sprinkle with cheese and Ritz cracker crumbs.
Return to oven until brown.

title: ham & cheese rolls
directions: Remove rolls from pan and slice in half.
Return bottom of rolls to pan.
Layer ham on top of rolls. Cover with cheddar and mozzarella cheese.
Replace top layer of rolls.
Press down slightly.
Cut into 12 servings.
Melt margarine and add onion, mustard, poppy seed and worcestershire sauce, and mix well.
Pour over top of rolls, spread all over, being sure all rolls have sauce on them.
Let set until topping is dry.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve as salad or dessert.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and cool whip.
Put into bottom of pie crust.
Spread pineapple over mixture, add sliced bananas, sprinkle pecans over all and top with cherries.
Chill and serve.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Prepare each tortilla by frying it in the hot oil in a frying pan over medium/high heat.
Fry each side of the tortilla for about 1 minute until crispy.
Drain the tortillas on paper towels. Combine the cinnamon and sugar in a small bowl.
Sprinkle half of the cinnamon mixture over both sides of the fried tortillas, coating evenly.
Not all of the sugar mixture will stick to the tortillas.
Combine the other half of the cinnamon mixture with the cornflake crumbs in another small bowl.
Pour the cornflake mixture into a wide, shallow bowl or onto a plate.
Place a large scoop of ice cream in the cornflake crumbs, and with your hands roll the ice cream around until the entire surface is evenly coated with cornflake crumbs.
You should not be able to see the ice cream.
Place the ice cream scoop on the center of the cinnamon/sugar coated tortilla.

title: taco soup
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Add taco seasoning; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes.
(I don't add the optional peppers, because it is already hot enough for my family.) Serve with corn chips, crackers or corn bread.
This makes a big pot full.

title: glorified rice salad
directions: Cook rice in salted water until soft.
Drain and cool.
Add sugar, marshmallows, pineapple and apples.
Cool 1 hour.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: stir-fry rice
directions: Saute steak until done, then pepper, carrots and onion.
Add rice and enough soy sauce to make rice brown.
Stir.

title: apricot almond tart
directions: You will need a flan pan, 11 1/4 x 8 x 1-inches, with a removable fluted rim.

title: divinity
directions: In large bowl, combine icing mix, corn syrup, vanilla and water.
Beat at high speed until stiff peaks form (approximately 5 minutes).
At low speed of mixer, mix in confectioners sugar.
Stir in nuts.
Drip by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let dry on top (approximately 10 hours), then turn so it can dry on other side. Place a half pecan on top.

title: german potato salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
In small saucepan, cook over medium heat the vinegar, water and cornstarch until thickened.
Pour over potato mixture and mix well.
Serve hot or cold.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook egg yolks, sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice, butter and salt until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream, drained fruit and marshmallows.
Chill 24 hours.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all together, but do not overbeat.
Lightly brown on one side (until bubbles show over all the top), then turn only once. Makes 15 to 20 pancakes.

title: salmon dip
directions: Drain salmon; remove and discard bones and skin.
Mash salmon; add remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Mix well; fold in sour cream.
Chill for at least one hour.
Makes 2 cups. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: spiced peach halves
directions: Drain peaches.
Add remaining ingredients to peach syrup and boil 2 to 4 minutes.
Pour at once over peach halves.
Let stand overnight.
Drain well and serve.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Boil over med. heat until thick.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Blend until creamy the butter, sugar and egg.
Beat in cream cheese, buttermilk or yogurt and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Beat well.
Roll into slight 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet 2 to 3-inches apart.
Using fork dipped in flour, press onto cookie and flaten slightly.
Sprinkle with colored sugars or a cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until set.
Do not brown!
Yields 60 (2-inch) cookies.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cover with water and bring to a boil for ten minutes. Turn down to simmer for 2 hours.

title: chicken rice chu-chu(a tex-mex style casserole)
directions: In a large skillet, saute the scallion, garlic and chicken in the oil until the pink is gone from the chicken.
Add the mushrooms, wine, herbs and seasonings.
Cook until the liquid is reduced.

title: portuguese breakfast meat
directions: Cut meat into 2 x 2-inch pieces; add all ingredients.
Mix well in large covered airtight bowl.
Stir and refrigerate couple of days.
After it's been in refrigerator 1 day, mix with hand in plastic glove.
Next day, mix again; let set in fridge for couple hours more, then fry a few pieces and taste.
Add more salt, if needed.
Freeze in small Baggies according to family size.
Most delicious with eggs for breakfast or with fried potatoes.
Enjoy.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine juice, lemonade, pineapple juice, and pineapple.
Add Ginger Ale and ice.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cooking Time:
45 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Temperature:

title: foil dinner
directions: Cut foil 12 x 12-inches square for each serving.
Place carrots and potato in center.
Cover with meat and onion.
Season and dot with butter.
Fold foil securely and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Just about any meat may be used for this dinner including pork chops, small steaks, hamburger patty, ham or smoked sausage.
Very delicious.

title: fiesta
directions: Brown meat. Drain. Add taco seasoning and water. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Prepare rice according to package directions. Melt Velveeta. Add to Ro-Tel tomatoes. Mix well. Combine meat, rice and cheese dip. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Top casserole with Doritos chips and bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes or until bubbly. Garnish with ring of lettuce, tomatoes and onions outside dish.

title: busy women's cookies
directions: Mix, spoon and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: buckeye cookie bars
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, oil and egg.
Beat until crumbly.
Stir in peanuts.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups and set aside. Press remaining mixture on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In medium bowl, beat milk and peanut butter.
Spread over crust. Sprinkle with reserved cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: holiday pecans
directions: Melt butter on cookie sheet at 325°.
Beat egg whites stiff. Add sugar to whites; beat.
Add pecans to egg white mixture and stir.
Spread pecans on cookie sheet.
Stir every 10 minutes to separate nuts.
Bake 30 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with salt. Cool and store airtight.

title: barbecued meats - turkish style
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix together well.
Shape into small links and barbecue.
They are excellent when stuffed in pita pocket bread, and you can add lettuce, tomatoes, or whatever you prefer.

title: hot pepper steamed mussels
directions: Scrub mussels and beard them. Heat oil in large, deep pan. Fry onions, garlic and ginger slowly until onions are golden.
Add chillies, turmeric and coriander.
Stir carefully for a few minutes.
Add salt and water and simmer covered for 5 minutes. Add mussels, cover and steam until mussels open.
Remove from heat and add fresh coriander.
Add lemon juice and salt to taste. Spoon liquid mixture into mussel shells and serve.

title: pueblo chili
directions: Brown meat and onion in oil; drain well.
Add water, barbecue sauce, tomato paste, chili seasoning, cumin and garlic.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Stir in beans, green peppers and rice.
Cook 15 minutes longer or until rice is done.

title: deviled corn
directions: Combine corn and water in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 7 to 8 minutes or just until corn is tender; drain.
Add butter, mustard, salt, pepper and hot sauce to corn.
Blend well.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated. Stir in cheese; serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: greek salad(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Tear lettuce into pieces and place in large bowl.
Add green onions, cucumber, tomatoes, green pepper, radishes, parsley, cheese and olives.

title: salisbury steak in crock-pot
directions: In a crock-pot put Lipton soup, mushroom soup and 1 can of water.
Stir and turn on high.
Take a mixture of seasoned flour and self-rising flour.
Coat steak.
Brown steak in a small amount of margarine.
Don't cook until done.
After steak is browned, put in crock-pot with gravy.
Cook on low approximately 3 hours or until steak is done.

title: pineapple tarts
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks which have been beaten.
Add baking powder to graham crackers; add vanilla to milk. Add graham crackers and milk alternately.
Beat egg whites and fold in mixture and fold in nuts.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: party croutons
directions: Melt oleo; mix with spices thoroughly.
Brush mixture on bread slices with pastry brush.
Cut bread into squares.
Place buttered side up on cookie sheet.
Bake at 200° for 4 hours.
Makes great croutons for soups and salads.
Keep in airtight container.

title: world's best carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat thoroughly and pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans or 1 (13 x 9-inch) pan.
Spraying with Pam works well too.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain well. Stir cheese which has been cut into squares and margarine into broccoli. When cheese and butter have melted, put into greased casserole dish.
Make a topping of crushed Ritz crackers and butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Layer in order given on large serving plate.
Cover and chill overnight.
When ready to serve, arrange tortilla chips around the dip.

title: spicy baked shrimp
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add shrimp and toss to coat.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Bake in 450° oven until shrimp are cooked through, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Garnish with lemon wedges and serve with French bread. Serves 2 to 4.

title: fresh coconut frosting
directions: Cook water and sugar until it threads, about 8 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add 2 tablespoons sugar to egg whites. Pour cooked mixture over egg whites and beat. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Use 2 packages of frozen coconut if fresh coconut is not available.
One large can drained crushed pineapple may be substituted for the coconut if you want pineapple frosting.

title: elyse's aloha cream
directions: Drain pineapple and cook rice.
Add to sugar and let sit for one hour.
Whip the cream until slightly thickened.
Fold into pineapple mixture until well blended.
Chill and serve.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour.
Make a smooth paste; stir constantly over fire until a rich brown, being careful not to burn.
Add water, tomatoes and okra (chopped fine).
Cook slowly for 1 hour. Add crab, oysters, shrimp (picked and deveined) and fish (minus bones and skin).
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add seasonings.
Soup should be thick.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. Chill.
Before serving, cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts on top.

title: slushy punch
directions: Add jello to hot water and sugar until dissolved, then add frozen juices with the water called for on cans.
Add pineapple juice.
Pour in gallon jugs and place in freezer.
Shake every hour, until frozen.
Allow 6 hours to thaw prior to serving so that it will still be slushy.
Yields 2 1/2 gallons.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters, reserving 1/4 cup liquor.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Spread a third of crumbs in 8x1 1/2 round pan.
Cover with half the oysters.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Using another third of the crumbs, spread a second layer; cover with remaining oysters.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Combine cream, reserved oyster liquor, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over oysters.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven (350) about 40 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients and chill at least 4 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix thoroughly until sugar breaks down the mayonnaise. Pour over cabbage slaw.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Using electric mixer, beat cake mix and egg yolks; add buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into three 8 or 9-inch cake pans (greased) and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool for frosting.
Use Cream Cheese Frosting.
Makes 1 cheese cake.
Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: I put it in the pan and make it with mommy and daddy.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Combine the butter and sugar and cream well.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix until combined.
Stir in Rice Krispies, chocolate morsels and raisins.
Drop by level tablespoonful onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.

title: bubbles
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Old tennis or racketball rackets make wonderful bubbles.
Kitchen utensils with holes are also fun to experiment with, such as slotted spoons, strainers and beaters. This is a great party activity!

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: In a medium pan over low heat, melt butter and add sugar, cocoa and milk, stirring constantly.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into eggs, then add eggs to mixture in pan.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle nuts on top and bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread and crumble real fine. Drain corn. Mix all ingredients together and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: fruit slush
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Mix well and freeze.
Serve slightly thawed.

title: green beans with sunflower seeds
directions: Snap ends off beans and break into 1/2-inch lengths.
If very young, leave whole.
Wash and place in pan.
Sprinkle onion, garlic, salt and pepper over beans.
Add water.
Cover tightly and cook on high until steaming; reduce heat and cook about 20 minutes until beans are crisp-tender.
Pour off excess liquid.
Sprinkle sunflower seeds and oregano over beans.
Mix lightly.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In saucepan, heat oil; add celery and onions.
Cook until tender.
In bowl, combine soup and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: chewy vegan carrot cake
directions: Place carrots, raisins, sugar, water and margarine in saucepan and bring to simmer over medium heat.
Continue to simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix well the ham, hamburger, egg, tomato juice, milk, oats and horseradish and shape into loaf.
Bake in moderate oven about 1 1/2 hours.
Baste with a mixture of brown sugar, vinegar, ground cloves and pineapple juice.

title: apple crisp ii
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Break egg into flour mixture; mix with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Melt 1/3 cup butter; cool to warm.
Drizzle over apples and topping.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: kooky cookies
directions: Mix by hand, cake mix, oil, water and eggs. Add nuts or morsels.
Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Reserve syrup from pineapple and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Pour in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat, add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add orange sherbet and stir until melted.
Chill until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg whites, about 20 minutes.
Fold in oranges and pineapple.
You can put oranges on top if you like.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour; beat eggs slightly.
Add cream-style corn and drained corn to sugar, flour and eggs. Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and 1 cup sugar 4 times.
Beat egg whites until frothy, then add cream of tartar and salt.
Beat until stiff. Fold in 1 cup sugar.
Fold in flour and sugar mixture.
Add extracts.
Bake in tube pan (fit bottom of angel food cake pan with brown paper), in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread or muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, walnuts, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in salad oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Stir liquid mixture into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Spread evenly in loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Let sit at least 4 to 6 hours prior to serving.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In a large bowl cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
Turn the batter in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon the pie filling onto the cake in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden and cake tests done.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crackers and 1 stick oleo.
Press in bottom of casserole dish and freeze for 15 minutes.
Mix sugar, 1 stick oleo and egg together for 10 minutes, then smooth over crust.
Top with bananas. Over bananas, put drained pineapple, then top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: suffern inn salad(24 hours)
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon and onion; add 2 cups of frozen peas and Swiss or Cheddar cheese strips, salt and pepper.
Chill for 24 hours.
Serve mixed with 2 cups torn lettuce and 8 slices bacon, crumbled.
Next day leftovers taste even better.
Serves 6.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes until soft.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Spoon out (leaving skin intact) middle; place in a mixing bowl.
Add purple onions, chopped green pepper, salt and pepper, egg, butter, milk and cheese.
Spoon mixture back into potato skin.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika, if desired.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Microwave for approximately 3 to 4 minutes (or until warm).
Serve with sliced ham and steamed broccoli.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, and baking powder. Add milk. Melt oleo in a 11 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle cinnamon or nutmeg over oleo if desired. Pour batter evenly over oleo then the add fruit with juice. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until light brown.

title: shrimp fritters
directions: Bring water to boil with butter.
Add flour all at once, stirring well until mixture leaves the side of saucepan.
Remove from heat and add well beaten eggs.
Stir until smooth and thick. Stir in shrimp and cheese.
Drop by small spoonfuls into shallow hot fat.
Brown on both sides.

title: macaroni hawaiian style
directions: Drain juices off of pineapple, oranges and cherries, saving the juice in 2-quart saucepan.
Mix eggs, salt, sugar and flour with the juice.
Cook until it thickens and turns a little clear. Set aside.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into
egg mixture.
Fold in apples, nuts or raisins.
Grease pan lightly.
Don't flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour at least.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Bronw meat and onion.
Drain off grease.
Add other ingredients and simmer.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine corn, egg, milk, salt and pepper.
Break up some crackers and fold into corn mixture.
Put into casserole dish. Crumble some crackers over the top and put a few pats of butter on the top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: neiman-marcus revenge cookies
directions: In blender, grind oatmeal to fine powder.
Cream butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add chips, candy and nuts.
Roll into ball and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Makes approximately 112 cookies.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix and bake in slow oven about 2 hours.

title: copper penny
directions: Cook carrots until tender. Drain. Combine carrots, green pepper and onion in a bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
They get better with age!

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt stick of margarine in baking dish and mix the first 4 ingredients together in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, then sprinkle dry muffin mix over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: portuguese bean soup(hawaiian style)
directions: Brown the Portuguese sausage and ham hock with the onion and garlic.
Add the stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce and water to cover. Simmer until ham hock is tender.
Add carrots and the 2 kinds of beans.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add to dashes of Worcestershire sauce.
Add cabbage about 5 minutes before serving.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in quart of water and 1 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Mix with cooked macaroni, relish, cheese, pimiento, celery and eggs. Mix together remaining salt, mayonnaise and dressing, mixing thoroughly with macaroni.
Serves 20.

title: sea island tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and chill.
Stir in salad dressing, which you have blended with sour cream and seasonings.
Gently stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Makes large dish.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Mix margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add gradually to egg mixture, beginning with flour, then milk, until all ingredients are mixed, ending with flour.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven.
Let cool in pan.

title: pancit
directions: Saute onions, vegetarian chicken (or real chicken) and garlic powder until cooked.
Add water, soy sauce (to taste) and chicken broth and let boil.
When boiling, add vegetables one after another or together and cook slightly.
Add rice noodles and let cook per package directions.
Add Accent, pepper and salt to taste.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add apples and remaining ingredients.
Mix quickly and thoroughly.
Place in oiled and floured 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cake is moist and requires no icing.
Serve with whipped cream or plain.

title: sausage squares
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and mayonnaise.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook 1 pound sausage and 1/2 cup chopped onions until tender.
Pour over biscuit mix.
Mix cheese, egg and mayonnaise.
Put on top of sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: mayfair salad dressing
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs and blend again.
Add the next 4 ingredients, blending well.
Then add oil very slowly, blending after each small addition of oil.
Store in refrigerator. Serve with your favorite salad or as a veggie dip.

title: refrigerator fudge
directions: Melt butter, cream cheese and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Add vanilla, sugar and nuts.
Mix well; press into ungreased pan.
Refrigerate until set up.

title: beef tips and rice
directions: Mix all together and cook all day in crock-pot on low.
Serve over cooked white rice.

title: margaret's potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes, cool and grate.
Heat 1/4 cup margarine and soup.
Add sour cream, onions and cheese. Add potatoes.
Place all in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine and mix with corn flake crumbs; sprinkle mixture over the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stono river crab quiche
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Place the cottage cheese, salt, eggs and white wine in a blender; blend at high speed until the mixture is creamy, about 2 minutes.
Transfer the egg mixture to a large bowl; stir in the crabmeat.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of the grated cheese over the bottom of the pastry shell; pour in the egg mixture.
Bake until the top is golden brown, about 45 minutes. Sprinkle the remaining cheese over the top of the quiche; return the pan to the oven just long enough to melt the cheese, about 5 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer half of the pork chops, onion, flour and cheese in casserole dish. Repeat with the other half. Save some cheese for top of casserole. Add milk to mushroom soup and pour over the top. Cook at 375° till done. Sprinkle with additional cheese the last 15 minutes.

title: chicken pastry
directions: Knead together until dough doesn't stick to fingers.
Let cool 1 hour.
Roll out until very thin; cut in strips.
Let set at least 1 hour or 30 minutes prior to meal.
Put in pot with boiling broth.
After all is in pot, cut off burner and let set on burner 15 minutes.

title: frozen california salad(preparation time: 15 minutes.)
directions: After mixing well with large spoon (do not use mixer), pour into cake pan and freeze.
Keep in freezer until 10 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares and serve.
Works great as a holiday salad.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt 12 ounces Velveeta with 2 sticks margarine and unsweetened chocolate.
Stir in corn syrup and vanilla.
Pour into a mixing bowl.
Stir in powdered sugar; beat until smooth.
Add nuts.
Spread in pan.
Store in cool place.
Makes 3 1/2 pounds.

title: scones
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, sugar and baking powder. Rub butter into flour mixture until it looks like breadcrumbs. Add raisins.
Add cold milk, mix with knife blade to form a soft dough.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness and cut into biscuit rounds. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff.
Cream yolks, sugar and nutmeg.
Add milk, ice cream, rum, brandy and whiskey.
Fold in egg whites.
Serve in punch bowl or pour into glass containers. Keep cold.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Mix the Jell-O, pie filling, water and sugar, then bring to a boil.
While hot, add the Coke/Pepsi.
Stir well and put into jello mold.

title: brownies with frosting
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, beating after each.
Mix in syrup, flour and nuts.
Mix and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Wash lettuce and dry.
Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces. Set aside.
Wash and peel cucumber and carrots.
Slice into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
In a deep dish begin layering lettuce, cucumber, carrots and celery.
Add layer of frozen peas and shredded cheese.
Top with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle mayonnaise with bacon bits.

title: pink punch
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar. Add orange juice and lemonade, then stir.
Finally, add the cold water.
This mixture may be frozen ahead of time.
Allow to thaw for 6 hours.
Mixture should be slushy.
Immediately before serving, add ginger ale or Sprite.
May garnish with orange or lemon slices.

title: grandma johnston's sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine together.
Add egg and vanilla. Mix well. Slowly add milk.
Mix all dry ingredients together and slowly add to sugar mixture.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together (1/3 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon) in a small bowl.
Roll cookie dough in ball and dip in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Pat out in pan. Bake at 400° until lightly brown.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: In a large bowl, beat margarine on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add about half of the flour, all the brown sugar, eggs, 2 teaspoons vanilla and the soda.
Beat on low until well mixed. Beat in remaining flour.
Stir in oats.

title: cheesy turkeyburgers
directions: Mix turkey, parsley, onion, garlic and pepper.
Shape into
5 patties.
Place on rack of broiler pan.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat for 6 to 7 minutes on each side or to desired doneness.
Top each patty with 2 slices of cheese.
Fill buns with lettuce, 1 tablespoon dressing, tomato and patty.
Makes 5 sandwiches.

title: taco spread
directions: Soften all cheeses.
Blend all ingredients together.
Serve with taco chips.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix well.
Will keep good in icebox or refrigerator.

title: spider cookies
directions: Melt the chips together over low heat.
After completely melted, add chopped nuts and chow mein noodles.
Place on wax paper until cooled.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add remaining ingredients, beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Stir flour, baking powder, soda and salt with electric beater at medium speed.
Blend shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat until light and fluffy, then at low speed, beat flour mixture alternately with bananas, just until smooth.
Turn into pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove.
Cool overnight before slicing.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix broccoli, walnuts and bacon bits.
In a separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli and place in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: marjorie's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven
to
Melt
butter
in	13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish
or sheet cake pan.
In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until
sugar
melts.
Cut
shortening
into flour until particles are
like
fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with fork until dough leaves the sides of the bowl.

title: aunt ludie's canned green beans
directions: Cook ham 1 hour, then add to green beans and cook 2 hours (cook down real low to get most of juice out).
Add sugar and vinegar.
Salt to taste.
Add a few chunks of ham per quart, then can.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together flour, margarine, powdered sugar and salt.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon rolls with bread starter
directions: Mix starter and 1 cup Bisquick and let stand for 1 hour. Add other cup of Bisquick to make dough. Knead and roll out into rectangles. Spread margarine on dough and sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Roll up and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Place in greased pan; let set for 15 minutes. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: grape kool-aid popsicles
directions: Mix Kool-Aid by instructions.
Pour into popsicle molds and freeze.
Can also be made into ice cubes.

title: orange-crush - pineapple ice cream
directions: Mix well and freeze.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat until sugar dissolves.
Cool and use to marinate 4 pounds of meat, ribs or chicken.
Yummy!

title: fruity salad
directions: Mix together sour cream, drained pineapple tidbits, drained fruit cocktail and drained mandarin oranges.
Add as many miniature marshmallows as you like.
Cover and chill.

title: cheesy egg burritos
directions: Melt butter in skillet over low heat.
Mix eggs and milk; pour into skillet.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until eggs begin to set.
Add cheese; continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted and eggs are set.
Fill tortillas with eggs, lettuce and tomatoes.
Roll up.
Serves 6.

title: corn curry
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add vegetables and curry powder. Cover and cook over low heat until vegetables are just tender (8 to 10 minutes).
Stir in sour cream and season to taste.
Heat, stirring constantly.
Yield: 4 servings.
(I usually double it; use 3 packages frozen whole kernel corn.)

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels on High for 3 minutes in the microwave.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in chow mein noodles until thoroughly coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let sit a few minutes until it hardens.

title: nacho dip
directions: Starting with refried beans (in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish), layer ingredients in the order they appear.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with plain nacho chips.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together first five ingredients.
Add sugar, oil and eggs, mix well.
Add carrots, drained pineapple and nuts.
Turn into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans or sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool full minute in pans, then turn out and cool on wire racks.
Fill layers and spread top and sides with Cream cheese Frosting.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Remove the meat from the bones in large pieces.
Dredge with flour seasoned with salt and paprika.
Brown in hot butter and put into a casserole dish.
Saute the onion, garlic and green pepper in the same butter for five minutes.
Mix the tomatoes and mushrooms into the onion mixture, season to taste with salt and pepper and pour over the chicken.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hawaiian dessert
directions: Melt oleo.
Add graham crackers (crushed).
Add 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix all items well and place in bottom of dish for shell.

title: homemade taco dip
directions: Simmer this for 30 minutes on low, then add 16 ounces Velveeta cheese (cubed).
Stir to make sure cheese does not stick or burn, then put in a crock-pot.

title: german slaw
directions: Alternate in large bowl cabbage and onions.
Sprinkle sugar over cabbage.
Boil the remaining ingredients for 2 to 3 minutes. Pour over cabbage and onion mixture.
Put in refrigerator for 12 hours before serving.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses, followed by egg and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut. Roll into
sugar and press down with a glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dinner-in-a-dish
directions: Cook beef
until
it turns light brown.
Add catsup and bring to	a
boil.
Add
kidney
beans, tomatoes, onion, green pepper and cheese.
Mix
all
together
and
put
in a 2 quart casserole dish.
Mix muffin mix together per box instructions. Pour over the ground
beef
and	bake at 375° until brown and muffin mix is done.

title: salmon (pie) casserole
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones.
With fork, mash salmon to remove large chunks.
Add olives, salt, pepper, sugar and 2 eggs (chopped).
Add salad dressing and mix well.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix in cranberry sauce. Then add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in walnuts and drained pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt butter.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix together with fork cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk.
Spread on top warm crust.
Add chopped pecans.
Over pecans, add Cool Whip.
Top this with cherry pie filling (in dabs first, then spread out).

title: swiss chicken cutlets
directions: *Or substitute 1/4 cup more broth.

title: october cake
directions: Mix together with beater and spread in a greased 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch pan.

title: meat-potato quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a 9-inch pie pan, stir together the oil and potatoes.
Press evenly into pie crust shape.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, until just beginning to brown, and remove from oven.
Layer on the cheese, chicken and onion.
In a bowl, beat together the milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture onto other ingredients.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of parsley flakes.
Return to oven and bake at 425° for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned and knife inserted 1 inch from the edge comes out clean.
Allow to cool 5 minutes before cutting into wedges.

title: snickerdoodles (cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly butter, shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Refrigerate (if desired).
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; roll balls in mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla, margarine, salt and evaporated milk. Bring to a rolling boil.
Let boil for 8 minutes.
Stir constantly.
After 8 minutes, remove from heat; add semi-sweet and chocolate chips, 3/4 of each bag.
Add 10 ounces marshmallows. Mix until melted together.
Pour into desired pan.
Sprinkle with nuts on top.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat; cool.
Add marshmallows and nuts to mixture.
Shape into 2 rolls, 1 1/2 to 2 inches in diameter.
Roll in coconut (optional).
Refrigerate several hours.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices when chilled.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cheesy pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in butter.
Place in casserole dish and pour remaining butter on top.
Season to taste.
Pour soups evenly over chops and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Serve rice on side.

title: hearty rice skillet
directions: In a large skillet, stir together beans, undrained tomatoes, vegetables, water, uncooked rice, thyme or dill weed, and, if desired, hot pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 12 to 14 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in soup; heat through.
Before serving, stir in almonds and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crumble crackers; add pecans, walnuts, dates, figs, raisins and cherries.
In large pan mix orange and grape juice.
Heat; add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Pour over cracker mixture and mix well.
Line cake pan with wax paper; press cake firmly in cake pan.
Store in icebox.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream brown sugar, granulated sugar, butter and oil together in large bowl.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk to sugar mixture and mix well.
Sift together all the dry ingredients (flour, allspice, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, and cocoa).
Add flour mixture to the sugar mixture and mix well.
Add grated zucchini and mix well.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 40 minutes at 375° until well done.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Combine milk and egg yolks.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils. Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/2 cup coconut, butter and vanilla.
Immediately pour filling into baked pastry shell.
Cover filling with waxed paper.

title: macaroni and beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet brown beef and set aside.
Saute onion in butter in beef fat.
Drain fat.

title: rose cake(1879)
directions: Beat to a cream the butter, sugar, flour and milk.
Add beaten egg whites.
Color 1/2 the batter pink.
Layer batter in 2 (9-inch) greased and floured pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer pink and white layers until all is used.
When all is in pan, cut down through, so colors will mix.
Bake at 350° until done (about 45 minutes).

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Using wax paper, shape into a ball.
Chill until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin oatmeal bars
directions: Grease baking pan, set aside.
Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir into mix.
Make well in center, add pumpkin, egg, butter and vanilla.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in raisins and peanuts.
Spread mixture into prepared pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven or until firm and slightly brown.
Let cool in pan.
Cut into bars.

title: coffee cream
directions: Combine water, salt and rice; cook as directed.
Stir in milk. Cover and cook over very low heat for 10 to 15 minutes, or until rice absorbs the milk.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in the sugar, marshmallows and coffee; cook, covered, over medium heat for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Mixture will be creamy.
Cover and cool.
When cool, whip the cream until stiff and fold this, together with the vanilla, into the rice mixture.
Serve topped with toasted nuts, shavings of unsweetened chocolate or chopped maraschino cherries.
Serves 8.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together oil and seasonings. Combine cabbage and green pepper; toss together with oil mixture. Place in 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Shake in a bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Place in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with pecans and raisins. Boil together butter and brown sugar until dissolved.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn upside-down on serving dish when removed from oven.

title: strawberry pretzels salad
directions: Pam spray a 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish. Mix margarine, brown sugar and pretzels. Cover bottom of Pyrex dish and cook at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: light harvard beets with carrots
directions: Wash beets. Place in large saucepan. Cover with cold water. Bring to boil. Boil for 30 to 45 minutes, until tender. Drain; slip off skins. Cut beets into 1/4 inch slices. In 2 quart saucepan stir together sugar, cornstarch and salt. Gradually stir in vinegar and water until smooth. Add margarine. Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute. Stir in beets and carrots until heated through. Ready to serve.

title: dressing
directions: Boil chicken until tender and reserve broth. Remove skin and bones and chop. Crumble cornbread and add to stuffing mix. Add other ingredients including chicken and mix together. Then mix in chicken broth until the mixture is very moist. If there is not enough of the broth from the chicken, you can use a can of broth. Put into a greased 9 x 13 pan or bowl and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chewy cookies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Cool. Store in tightly sealed container.

title: vegetable scallop
directions: Melt butter or margarine in saucepan; remove from heat; blend in flour, mustard, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce - stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sauce thickens and boils one minute.
Add peas, beans and onions - turn into buttered 8 cup baking dish.
Make a rim of bread crumbs around edge of dish; sprinkle cheese over.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 min., or until top is bubbly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss broccoli, onion, raisins, nuts and bacon.
Mix remaining ingredients for dressing and put on salad 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: italian liver and onions
directions: Mix bread, cheese, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic; dip liver 1 piece at a time into buttermilk, then in crumb mixture.
Spray baking sheet with nonstick spray.
Transfer liver to sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Saute sliced onion with butter until golden.
Serve with liver.

title: marinara sauce with shellfish
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil in a large skillet until garlic begins to turn lightly brown.
Add tomatoes, anchovy paste, wine, parsley, oregano, bay leaves, pepper and salt and heat to simmer. Continue simmering for approximately 15 to 20 minutes and remove from heat.
Sauce can be prepared in advance and placed in refrigerator until needed.
Steam and peel shrimp and put aside. Steam mussels and clams until they open and put aside.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Cut up head of lettuce in fine pieces.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer next four ingredients in pan.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar together; spread on salad in pan.
Sprinkle on cheese.

title: corn salsa
directions: First you buy it.
Then you boil it.
Put it on a plate.
Eat with butter and salt.
Yum!

title: our christmas eve punch
directions: In a punch bowl, pour juice and soda.
Add spoonfuls of sherbet.
Stir just to mix.
Vanilla ice cream may be used instead of orange sherbet.

title: baked lasagna - mama - mia
directions: In hot water add salt and olive oil and bring to a rolling boil in large pan.
Add lasagna noodles, cook till just tender, it will absorb moisture later.
Drain noodles and run cold water over them until cold.
In greased 9 x 13 x 2 pan cover the bottom of the pan with some of the lasagna filling which you mixed prior and then a thin layer of sauce.
Sprinkle with part of the grated romano/parmesan cheese; then a sprinkling of mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers, finishing off with noodles on top.
Pour more sauce over the top and sprinkle with parmesan/romano cheese and top with mozzarella cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in 375° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cornbread, onion and seasonings in a large bowl.
Mix well. Blend in broth, butter and milk.
Mixture will be very soft to allow for loss of moisture during baking. Add more broth if necessary.
Spoon dressing into a greased pan. Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until well browned.
Serves 12.

title: meat filling for fatayer
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place 1 1/2 tablespoons of filling in center of each circle and pinch edges together to form triangle. Place pies side by side in a lightly oiled baking pan.
Bake at 400° until bottoms are browned (approximately 20 minutes).
Place under broiler to brown tops if necessary.

title: stuffing for shrimp
directions: Stuff 4 large shrimp; sprinkle with butter.

title: peanut butter
directions: Pour roasted peanuts into a blender; add peanut oil and salt. Blend until mixture becomes spreadable.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine
flour,
salt,	pecans	and cheese in bowl.
Add butter, beat
well.
Shape in half; then roll each into 10 inch long
rolls.
Wrap	in waxed paper.
Chill 2 hours.
Slice into 1/4
inch
slices.	Cook on greased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy onion-cheese spread
directions: Bake in a low pan (round 12 to 14-inch Corning Ware) for 15 to 30 minutes or until edges are browning.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and press into a 10-inch pie pan.
Combine the next 4 ingredients.
Beat the 5 egg whites and fold in or put on top (like lemon pie).
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serve chilled.

title: pear preserves
directions: Fill dish pan to 1/4 inch from top of pan.
Add 10 pounds of sugar over the top and let sit overnight.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients into large bowl and set aside.
In blender container, blend 1 c. carrots with 1 egg and 1/2 c. oil.
Repeat twice and adding nuts and extra egg with last blending.
Combine with dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir by hand, no mixer needed.
Pour into well greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and frost.

title: grandma's casserole noodle lasagna
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Add ground meat, Accent, pepper and sugar.	Stir
in
whole
tomatoes, tomato sauce and water. Simmer over low flame for 15 minutes.

title: super-fast spinach saute
directions: In a large frying pan with a lid, heat the olive oil over medium heat.
Add the garlic and cook 1 to 2 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix in order and bake on greased and floured cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn paper towel with powdered sugar on it over cake roll (leave towel on).
Then roll up on a rolling pin and let cool about 15-20 minutes.

title: pineapple cherry dump cake
directions: Pour undrained pineapple into a buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Pour cherry pie filling over this and sprinkle cake mix over top. Sprinkle nuts and coconut on top of this.
Cut margarine into thin patties and arrange on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Check the cake at 35 minutes.
If not done, continue 4 to 5 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip, if you wish.

title: hot chili
directions: Cook meat with onion and peppers in pan until meat browned, then put all ingredients in pot.
Bring to a boil, then let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: french onion bake
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions in 2 Tablespoons butter until tender.
Sprinkle with flour;
stir in salt and pepper.
Add the consome and sherry;
cook and stir until thickened, about 3 minutes.
Pour into a shallow 2-quart baking dish or individual baking dishes.
Spread remaining butter on both sides of bread; place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350°F. for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Place bread on top on onion mixture; sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake , uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: crispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Stir in creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, dates and nuts.
Form into small balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly, then remove from cookie sheet.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: easy baklava
directions: Mix nuts, sugar and cinnamon together.
Melt butter.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place six buttered sheets in pan.
Sprinkle generously with walnut mixture.
Add three more buttered filo sheets.
Sprinkle with nut mixture.
Continue alternating buttered filo with nut mixture until nut mixture is used.
Top layer of filo should have 6 to 7 sheets.
Pour melted butter over assembled Baklava and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: black pepper steak
directions: Place steak in a large shallow dish.
Combine onions, vinegar, oil, brown sugar, garlic, salt, marjoram, rosemary and hot sauce; pour over steak.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove steak from marinade.
Press 2 teaspoons pepper onto each side of steak.
Grill over hot coals 15 minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness.
Place steak on serving platter; garnish with tomato wedges and fresh parsley.
To serve, cut into serving pieces.
Yield:
3 to 4 servings.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs. Put in a greased casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave applesauce
directions: Microwave apples on High for 8 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Can be frozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Mix in beaten egg mixture.
Add pumpkin.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Let cream cheese set at room temperature for about 1 hour. Mix with mayonnaise and mix well.
Add vegetables and salt.
Mix well.

title: dilled apple and potato salad
directions: Rinse potatoes, but do not peel.
Cut each in half.
Place in saucepan and add water just to cover.
Cover and cook 10 minutes over medium heat.
Add carrots and cook 10 minutes more or until vegetables are tender, but firm.
Drain and rinse gently with cool water.
Drain again and set aside to cool.
Cut potatoes into bite sized pieces.
Set aside.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheeses together until well blended; add other ingredients except pecans.
Shape into balls.
Roll in pecans. Wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serve with crackers and chips.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: In 8-inch round baking dish, combine zucchini, cheese and tomato sauce.
Heat covered in microwave 8 to 9 minutes until tender, stirring once.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese and let stand covered 5 minutes before serving.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend together.
Top with caramel topping (not too thick). Dip slices in the dip.
Granny Smith apples are good to use.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in a saucepan.
Add milk to egg yolks and mix.
Combine with dry ingredients; stir well.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir slowly all
during cooking time.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Use 3 egg whites for meringue.
Sprinkle a bit of coconut on top before baking.

title: mom's prize winning meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack firmly into ungreased loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches).
Bake in a preheated oven (350°) for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting slices.
Makes 8 servings.

title: casserole of vegetables
directions: Mix everything together except oleo and crackers.
Spread in greased 8 1/2 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Mix crushed crackers and oleo together and sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
In a small bowl, beat pumpkin, oil, juice, eggs and vanilla.
Stir pumpkin mixture into flour mixture until well combined.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Turn into prepared pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Turn out of pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar before slicing.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all.
Pour into 10 x 10 x 2-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until brown.
Cut into squares.
Good warm or cold.
Good with ham.
Quite rich.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet; drain grease.
Brown green pepper, celery and onion in skillet until tender.
Mix these ingredients with the soup, water and rice.
Place in buttered casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes at 350° covered with aluminum foil.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla together, then add flour, salt and soda, then add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lemon frozen pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with beater, adding sugar.
Beat (in double boiler) over boiling water until thick, about 3 minutes.
Remove; add rind and juice.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in first mixture.
Whip cream and fold all together.
Line tray with wax paper.
Sprinkle half of crumbs on bottom.
Pour in mixture and put remaining crumbs on top.
Freeze at least 3 hours.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Cut chicken from bone and grind fine.
Mix all ingredients and press in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: 6-weeks bran muffins
directions: Pour 2 cups bran cereal in large mixing bowl; add boiling water and stir. Let stand to cool. Add sugar and oil. Stir in eggs. Add dry ingredients and buttermilk. Add other cup bran last and raisins if using. Spray muffin tins. Bake at 400° about 18 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Blend in blender until thick and creamy.
Yield: 3/4 cup.

title: marinated beans
directions: Heat oil, sugar, vinegar and salt until dissolved.
Let cool. Add to beans and onion.
Marinate 12 to 24 hours.
Drain and serve.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.
Enjoy!

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Pour cold water over them.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add mix, stirring in well.
Add tomato paste, sauce and water.
Simmer.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese, sauce, Cheddar and then Mozzarella.
Repeat layers two more times.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in oven-safe dish. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Boil chicken in water seasoned with broth cubes.
Cool chicken, then skin and debone (save broth).
Heat mushroom soup with enough broth to make sauce thin enough to pour.
Add onions and vegetables and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheeses in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 10 servings.

title: pumpkin centerpiece cake
directions: Beat the cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in confectioners sugar, vanilla and food coloring.
Beat mixture until it holds together.
Chill 10 minutes.
Form some of the mixture into leaves and place on top of cake.
Spoon remaining around bottom to form grass.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Use for fresh cucumbers and onion salad.
Adjust the vinegar to taste.
Blend until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers and onion.
Cover and let tastes blend.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix together; sprinkle more grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream 1 cup of sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Add rind of lemon.
Add flour all at once; add milk, then add baking powder and salt.
Pour into greased pan; bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Shape into balls. Roll balls in coconut.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar and cook 2 minutes.
Add milk and bring to a boil; remove from heat and cool.
Add sugar slowly, until spreading consistency.

title: other mama's cranberry salad
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and boiling water. Stir well. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into mold. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: cranberry crunch pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and spices.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add to dry ingredients alternately with vinegar and melted butter.
Mix well.
Stir in cranberries and pecans.
Bet egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into cranberry mixture and blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: sauteed cherry tomatoes
directions: Heat the butter in large saute pan.
When the butter is foaming, add the tomatoes.
Toss them over high heat, shaking the pan back and forth for about 3 minutes and sprinkling the tomatoes with the sugar (this gives them a shiny glaze).
Do not overcook or the skins will split and the tomatoes will be too soft.
Season with salt and pepper; garnish with parsley.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Simmer raisins and water for approximately 15 minutes.
Add salt, baking soda and butter.
Let cool.
Then mix together eggs, sugar, vanilla and flour and add to raisin mixture, mixing well. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or may use 1 or 2 pound coffee cans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Put pan of water in bottom of oven.

title: salmon pie
directions: Drain and debone salmon.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in deep uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add onions and garden peas, if desired.

title: friendship tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.	Store mix in an airtight container.
To serve, place 1 1/2 tablespoon of mix in a cup. Add 1 cup boiling water and stir well.
Yield: 50 servings.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Boil 3 minutes.
Line pan with aluminum foil.
Spoon on graham crackers and cook 8 minutes at 325°.
Put 1 cup of chopped nuts on crackers.

title: crock-pot soup
directions: Put all ingredients into a crock-pot.
Turn on high until mixture starts to boil.
Turn on low and cook all day.

title: golden chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken.
Pour marinade over chicken and let stand in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours. Start heating oven to 425°.
With fork, lift chicken out of marinade and arrange in 1 layer in greased, shallow, open pan. Dot chicken with 1/4 cup of butter or margarine.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Turn and baste every 10 minutes.
Spoon any pan drippings over top.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: congo squares
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° no more than 35 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: wayne's favorite fudge
directions: Stir together sugar, margarine and milk in heavy pan; bring to full bubbling boil.
Boil 5 minutes (medium heat), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and stir until melted; add vanilla.
Add Marshmallow Creme and stir until mixed.
Add nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and let cool overnight.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine yeast and warm water; allow to stand 5 minutes until it foams, then stir down.
Melt butter in pan.
Add milk immediately and remove from heat.
Blend in sugar, eggs, salt and dissolved yeast.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Cover and allow to rise until double, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: coffee punch
directions: Blend coffee and half of coffee ice cream to a very thick consistency.
Chill in refrigerator at least 2 hours.

title: ricotta cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, cheese and salt.
Stir in sifted flour and baking soda.
If sticky, add a little more flour.
Roll into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 10 minutes at 350°.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of hot water.
Add 1 cup cold water. Mix cream cheese and Pet milk together until smooth.
Chill.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with shortening.
Beat eggs until fluffy in a large bowl.
Add sugar, vanilla and margarine, beating until creamy.
Combine flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix at low speed. Spread evenly in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, mayonnaise, mushroom soup, onion and egg well together.
Stir in stuffing.
Pour in dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Pour on melted margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sausage mushroom breakfast casserole
directions: Spread croutons in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Set aside.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Sprinkle sausage over croutons.
Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients.
Mix well and pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Remove from refrigerator.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake an additional 1 to 5 minutes until cheese melts.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes and parsley, if desired.

title: my favorite lemonade
directions: In large glass jar, combine lemon juice and sugar; stir to dissolve.
Add water and blend well.
Pour over ice and add sliced lemons to serve.

title: rosy morning rhubarb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, pineapple, lemon juice and rhubarb; cook on stove until boiling.
Remove and mix in slightly beaten egg yolks and tapioca, cook some more.
Pour mixture in baked pie shell and place in preheated 350° oven while beating egg whites for meringue.
Add 2 teaspoons sugar to egg whites and beat.
Remove pie from oven and top with meringue.
Return to oven for a few minutes of browning.

title: sweet and sour sausage balls
directions: Mix together the sausage, bread crumbs and eggs; form small balls.
Brown in skillet.
Remove.
In same skillet, brown pineapple and green pepper in sausage drippings.

title: mexico omelet
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased frying pan and cook.

title: economy cocoa
directions: Mix thoroughly. Store in airtight container.
Use as needed. Use 1/4 cup of mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: 5-layer delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and a cup of nuts together and press in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° until light brown.
Let cool.
Mix one of the pudding mixes according to the directions on the box.
Layer it over the top of the crust. Mix cream cheese, 1/3 of the Cool Whip and powdered sugar together and put over the top of the previous pudding.
(If mixture is too thick to spread, add a little more Cool Whip.)
Mix the other box of pudding together and put over the top of the cream cheese mixture.
Put Cool Whip on top and decorate with nuts and cherries.

title: layered shrimp dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and 3 tbsp. salsa; spread into ungreased 9 inch pie plate.
Combine cocktail sauce and remaining salsa; spread over cream cheese.
Place shrimp evenly over top.
Sprinkle with olives.
Combine cheeses; sprinkle over olives.
Top with onions.
chill. Serve with tortilla chips.
Yield 12 - 16 servings.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients into a large saucepan.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve with crackers or eat alone.
Easy and good.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Place potatoes into 2 large resealable plastic bags.
Combine the parmesan cheese and seasonings add to potatoes and shake to coat.
Pour oil into two 15 x 10 x 1 in baking pan.
Pour potatoes into pans.
Bake uncovered at 375 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Yields:
12 to 14 servings.

title: pecan supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
In a medium bowl combine flour, soda, salt and oats. mix well with wire whisk and set aside.
In a large bowl blend sugars with an electric mixer at medium speed. Add butter and mix to form a grainy paste.
Scrape down sides of bowl, then add eggs and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until fully combined.
Add the flour mixture, pecans and chocolate chips, and blend at low speed just until combined.
Do not overmix.
Drop dough by rounded tbsp onto ungreased cookie sheets, 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake for 18-20 minutes.
Immediately transfer cookies with a spatula to a cool, flat surface.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: grandma holley's jelly cake
directions: Bake 4 layers, following cake mix directions.
Cool layers until just slightly warm.
Spread each layer generously with jelly.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased muffin pans.
Do not have to rise.
These are good.

title: perfect meat loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients thoroughly with 1 can of tomato sauce.
Pack mixture firmly into loaf pan.
Chill about 1 hour. Unmold into a shallow baking pan.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour second can of sauce over loaf.
Bake 20 minutes more.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs, zucchini, vanilla and nuts.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes coarsely.
Mix all other ingredients.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole (ungreased) at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fruit tacos
directions: Add milk and pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add Cool Whip to pudding mixture.
Just before serving, spoon pudding mixture into taco shells.
Top with fruit and coconut.
Pour small amount of chocolate syrup over top. Makes 8 tacos.

title: tasty crackers
directions: Put crackers in a large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to crackers.
Mix well and enjoy!

title: apricot nut squares
directions: Heat water, milk and 1 tablespoon sugar; let cool and put aside.
When cool, dissolve 1 package dry yeast.
Mix as pie dough the flour, oleo and egg yolks.
Add yeast mixture and divide into 3 parts.
Roll between wax paper and lay on pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix ground nuts, cinnamon and 1 cup sugar and put 1 cup aside.

title: hearty potato soup(serving size: 10)
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in Dutch oven.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in the hot water and add to potato mixture.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; cover and reduce
heat to simmer for 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Dissolve flour in 1/4 cup milk and stir into soup.
Add remaining milk and cook over medium heat until thickened, about 25 minutes.

title: hamburger noodle casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Drain.
Brown hamburger in margarine.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream and onion.
In a buttered 2-quart casserole, spread half the noodles; cover with the cheese mixture, then cover with the remaining noodles.
Pour hamburger mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: candied strawberries
directions: Thoroughly
blend gelatin and milk. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Refrigerate overnight. Form into strawberries and roll in sugar. Add leaves.

title: great glogg
directions: Combine 3 cups dry, red wine, cinnamon, cloves, orange peel, kiwi, raisins and nuts in medium saucepan.
Cover and simmer over very low heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Do not allow mixture to boil. Remove from heat and let stand at room temperature 45 minutes to steep.

title: fresh pigs' feet
directions: Clean pigs' feet.
Combine ingredients.
Cover with water and boil over medium heat until tender.
May be necessary to add water during cooking, however, add a small amount at a time once almost tender.
Allow most of the water to cook out, causing the remaining liquid to be rather sticky.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Stir the first 4 ingredients until mixed and melted, then add eggs one at a time, stirring in each one.
The mixture will be runny, so have your fire low and keep stirring until you start getting it lumpy.
Keep cooking until it is thick.
It takes a lot of stirring and elbow muscle.
(Mixture will turn a dull color so you will know it is done.)
After mixture is done, take a teaspoonful and dip it in boiling chicken broth.
Cover; it takes about 20 minutes per kettle.
(I usually put in about 12 to 18 dumplings at a time.)
Once in awhile, I will put in that instant chicken broth in my dumpling mixture to give it more taste.
When I do that, I add about 1 teaspoon of milk.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together.
Divide in half; set aside.
Mix together salmon, onion, cracker crumbs, lemon, pepper and half the mayonnaise-sour cream mixture.
Place in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 3/4 of an hour.
Mix the cucumber into the other half of the mayonnaise-sour cream mixture and use for a sauce on the loaf.

title: rabbit stew
directions: First cook the rabbit in salt water to which a small onion, cut up is added.
When it is cooked enough so that it won't fall from bones (save broth), fry it in butter or margarine.
Remove meat from the bones.
Put back into broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add a lump of butter and enough milk so it doesn't look cloudy.
Serve heated through.

title: coffee crunch popcorn
directions: Butter sides of a heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugar, butter, corn syrup, coffee and salt.
Bring to boiling.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and nuts in a 17 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan.
Stir to coat.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 15 minutes.
Stir.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Stir before serving.
Makes 10 cups.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Add cocoa, stir until well blended.
Remove from heat and add sugar, eggs and vanilla, mixing well.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Stir cranberry sauce in jello mixture (jello and water) until it melts or dissolves; use mixer on low speed.
Mix all ingredients together.
Jell in refrigerator.

title: bacon mini loaves
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except bacon.
Shape into 6 loaves.
Crisscross bacon strips over loaves.
Place on broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine well. Add 5 egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each. Alternately add flour, buttermilk, soda and coconut. Beat 5 egg whites until stiff and fold into batter. Add vanilla. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done. Makes three 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: peanut butter pinwheels
directions: Cream the shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar and corn syrup and mix thoroughly.
Add beaten egg.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Chill 2 hours and then shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place each ball on a greased baking sheet.
Press the balls flat with a floured fork.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for about 12 minutes or until done.

title: spatzle's(german noodles)
directions: Knead ingredients together until dough does not stick to bowl. Dough should not be sticky or too hard.

title: ranch beans
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet. Saute beef and onion in melted butter until beef is browned.
Add salt, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine sugar and ketchup. Add beans and beef mixture to brown sugar mixture.
Turn into 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad on lettuce leaf
directions: Mix mayonnaise, curry powder, lemon juice and soy sauce. Combine all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serves 25.

title: party punch
directions: Put sherbet in punch bowl and pour in equal amounts of orange drink and ginger ale. It will melt the sherbet and be foamy. It is delicious!

title: slush
directions: Brew 8 tea bags in 2 cups boiling water.
In a large bowl, mix together lemonade, orange juice, liquor and 7 cups of boiling water.
Combine all ingredients together.
Freeze 2 days before using.
Spoon in glass and add ginger ale or 7-Up.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: barbecue
directions: Saute onions in butter and ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: easy enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onions with the meat.
While beef is cooking, warm beans in a big pot.
Drain meat and add to the beans; heat to boiling, then turn heat off and set aside.
Pour enchilada sauce in a shallow pan.
Spray or grease the bottom of a square cake pan. Dip tortillas in the enchilada sauce and place in square pan until bottom of pan is covered.
Add a layer of meat and bean mixture, then cheese.
Layer additional tortillas and repeat all other ingredients.
Bake about 45 minutes to 1 hour at around 350°. Serves 6.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan in a 350° oven.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour over melted butter.
Pour fruit (undrained) over that.
Bake about an hour, or until dough rises to the top and turns golden brown.

title: easy peanut butter candy
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening over warm water (turn fire off before adding chocolate) in double boiler.
Add the peanut butter. Stir well.
Pour into a 9-inch wax paper lined dish. Cut when cool.
May use dark, white or butterscotch coating chocolate for this recipe.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Combine everything in a bowl and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until nicely browned and firm to touch.
Cut into squares.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Use double boiler.
Make sauce of oleo, flour, milk, salt, paprika and pepper.
Add most of the grated cheese and let cook until melted.

title: brown and serve rolls(makes 24 to 32 rolls)
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in margarine, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
In a small bowl mix yeast and water.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Stir into milk when it has cooled, then add half the flour.
Beat until smooth, then work in remaining flour.
Turn onto floured board and knead about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn over, cover and let rise until doubled, about an hour. Punch down.
Form into any shape of rolls you wish (Parker-House, Cloverleaf, small dinners rolls).
Arrange on greased cookie sheets or in a pan.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes until partly baked, but not browned.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except potato chips.
Grease a baking dish.
Crumble 1/2 potato chips in bottom of dish.
Pour mixed ingredients over potato chips.
Crumble other 1/2 potato chips on top.
Bake in a 300° oven for 55 or 60 minutes.

title: hot dog s'mores
directions: Combine 1/4 cup potato flakes with butter.
Split franks in half lengthwise.
Place half of franks on cookie sheet, cut side up with sides touching.
Prepare 4 servings mashed potatoes as directed on package, decreasing water to 3/4 cup.
Add egg.
Spread potatoes over franks; top with 2 or 3 slices cheese.
Cover with remaining franks.
