Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with buttered potato flakes.
Secure with wooden picks.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade pumpkin pie spice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container. Use as a substitute for the spices called for in your favorite pumpkin pie recipe.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. In large bowl, combine all the ingredients and beat until well mixed. This will be a sticky, thick mixture.
It is easier to roll the dough if it is divided into two or three portions.
Spoon out each portion of dough and place it on a well-floured surface. Sprinkle a little flour on top of the dough and carefully form it into a disk.
Don't work too much flour into the dough because you want a crisp (short-type) cookie. Roll the dough to a thickness of about 1/4 inch.

Cut with a 3-inch cookie cutter. Place the cookies on ungreased cookie sheet, spacing the cookies about 2 inches apart. Teacakes don't have to be uniform in shape, so don't worry if each cookie is not round. Repeat with the remaining dough. Bake for 7 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned on top.
Remove to a rack to cool. Store in an airtight container.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Pare, core and slice apples.
Place in crust.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Dot with butter.

title: sugar-free peanut butter pie
directions: Mix instant pudding by directions on box.
Fold in peanut butter and vanilla.
Last, fold in lite Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Keep in freezer.

title: puppy chow
directions: Take large plastic grocery bag and pour 2 cups powdered sugar in it. Put Crispix cereal in large bowl. Melt together butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips. Stir until well mixed. Pour immediately over cereal and stir well until cereal is coated. Now pour mixture into grocery bag and shake vigorously. Add last cup powdered sugar and shake again.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and liquids.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done in center.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and chill.
When ready to serve, add lime sherbet and ginger ale.

title: cocoons
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla; beat until light.
Mix dry ingredients and cream mixture and blend thoroughly.
Shape.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in 325° oven.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook, covered, 1/2 hour in 400° oven.

title: green peas delicious
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper in margarine.
Put ingredients in casserole.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spicy ravioli and cheese
directions: Place bell peppers in baking dish; sprinkle with oil, seasoned salt, garlic powder and sugar.
Broil 15 minutes or until tender and browned, turning once.
Prepare ravioli according to package directions.

title: kristy's spicy meat loaf
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Place in pan; rub a little barbecue sauce on top of meat loaf.
Place in oven and bake.

title: old fashioned coconut pie
directions: Blend butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vinegar, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until light brown.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a 12 cup muffin pan.
Sift and measure flour.
Sift again with sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat egg in medium bowl.
Blend in sour cream and milk. Add dry ingredients and melted butter all at once, stirring just until moistened.
Fill each muffin cup 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: Melt chocolate baking squares in pan on stove or in microwave. Dip strawberries in chocolate. Lay on wax paper to allow chocolate to harden.

title: pasta and vegetables(escarole, sausage and beans)
directions: Cut and clean escarole.
Let soak a few minutes.
Place sausage in a frying pan with oil and brown.
When sausage is almost done, put in garlic and escarole with 1 cup water.
Stir around until mixed with sausage.
Stir in beans.
Boil pasta and drain.
Toss sausage mix into pasta; add cheese.

title: orange chicken cutlets
directions: Rinse and dry cutlets; flour and season.
Heat margarine in skillet; brown cutlets 3 minutes each side.
Set aside.
In a small dish; mix honey, orange juice and onions.
Heat in a small pan; add cornstarch blended with water and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Pour over cutlets.
Makes 4 servings.
Low cholesterol.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the butter and cheese.
Blend in egg yolk and vanilla. Add dry cake mix 1/3 at a time; mix well after each addition.
If using a mixer, add last part of cake mix by hand.
Chill dough 30 minutes.
(Can be chilled overnight.)
Heat oven to 375°.
Finish cookies in one of the following ways:
Use a cookie press to shape cookies on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 9 minutes until delicately browned.
Cool cookies before removing from baking sheet.
Or, drop by scant teaspoonful on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool before removing from baking sheet.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Put through grinder or blender all the ingredients.
Make into small balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in flour, then dip into an egg and milk batter, then roll in cracker crumbs.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: apple pie slices
directions: Crumble flour, salt and Crisco.
Roll out 1/2 of dough and put on cookie sheet.
Add sliced apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Frost with powdered sugar and milk.

title: tiger butter
directions: Combine white chocolate and peanut butter in a double boiler. Heat and stir until melted.
Spread mixture on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan lined with wax paper.
Pour melted semi-sweet chocolate over peanut butter mixture and swirl through with a knife.
Chill until firm.
Cut in 1 1/2 x 1-inch pieces.
Store in a cool place.
Makes about 6 dozen pieces.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and sugar.
Cut Crisco into flour mixture, adding yeast and buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly and let rise 1 hour in refrigerator. Shape into biscuits or use biscuit cutter.
Bake in 400° oven until brown.
(Dough will keep in covered container in refrigerator for 4 to 5 days.)

title: polish bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla in a bowl. Add the rest of the ingredients. Then add flour until manageable. Add nuts, etc. When dough resembles cookie dough, knead until tacky to hands. Place dough in warm place, covered, until doubled (3 to 4 hours). Knead. Place in pans. Let rise 3 to 4 hours. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour. Butter tops and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: liver loaf
directions: Brown beef liver in hot fat.
Put
through
food chopper with pork
sausage.
Add
bread
crumbs,
minced
onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, salt,
pepper, celery, salt, eggs and bouillon.	Top with bacon slices.	Place in buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch buttered loaf pan.
Bake at
for 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: chicken-mushroom
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter, chicken broth, garlic, wine and remaining ingredients.
Set aside in small bowl.
Add 2 teaspoons butter and stir-fry chicken tenders, turning often, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour over chicken and simmer until tender, 3 to 5 minutes.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Blend all ingredients except zucchini and chocolate chips. Fold in zucchini and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan for thick or 10 x 15-inch for thin ones.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apricot jam(sugar-free)
directions: *Or any other dried fruit without sugar (apples are great).

title: minute steak
directions: Place steak in bottom of pan. Cover with soups and onion.
Dot with butter.
Cook 30 minutes at 300°.
Serves 6.

title: fattoush
directions: Cut pita breads into halves.
Cut each half into 8 wedges. Place on a shallow baking pan.
Bake until crisp, turning occasionally, about 25 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.
In a large bowl, combine lettuce, cucumber, Feta cheese, onion, tomatoes and pita wedges.
Mix vinaigrette dressing, parsley and mint.
Pour over salad mixture and toss.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix well. Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine the two mixtures. Add vanilla, raw apples and nuts.
Lightly oil a 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan.
Pour in cake and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: pizza bread
directions: Thaw bread overnight in refrigerator or on counter, 6 to 8 hours.
Roll out loaf to about 9 x 13-inch rectangle.
Brush egg on center 1/3 of the bread.
Pour 1/2 can tomato sauce on top of the egg. Place 1/2 of pepperoni, hamburger and 1/2 of both cheeses and mushrooms on.
Fold sides to center and seal ends.
Brush top with egg.
Repeat with other loaf.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Slice and serve hot.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, beating until fluffy.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain beans for 10 minutes or until as much liquid as possible is drained.
Mix beans with remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or in microwave for about 10 minutes, stirring once during cooking.
Cover before cooking.

title: italian antipasto
directions: Mix vinegar, water, garlic, dressing mix and pepper.
Bring to boil; add vegetables.
Simmer and stir 8 minutes.
Add oregano. Cool, then refrigerate in a jar or other container.

title: foundation cake
directions: Cream softened butter thoroughly in deep bowl.
Add sugar, gradually beating, until the mixture is fluffy and light (like whipped cream).
Add eggs to creamed butter and sugar.
Beat until light.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with liquid to creamed butter and sugar.
Begin and end with dry ingredients.
Add flavoring and blend thoroughly.

title: stroganoff meatballs
directions: Make meatballs, cook on top of stove in frying pan or in oven until done.
Drain well.

title: frozen cranberry ambrosia
directions: Combine ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Freeze.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix in bowl the eggs, oil, brown sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Combine in separate bowl the flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nuts and raisins.
Add wet mixture to dry mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into two 8 x 5-inch greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for about 70 minutes.

title: polish pecan cookies(ciastka kurche)
directions: Cream butter with vanilla extract; add confectioners sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add water and beat thoroughly. Add flour in fourths, mixing until blended after each addition. If necessary, chill the dough until easy to handle.

title: baked meat pies
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and pepper.
Drain fat.
Add salsa, tomato sauce, parsley, salt, pepper, cayenne and sweet basil.
Simmer and stir.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Roll Pillsbury 1869 brand buttermilk refrigerator biscuits flat.
Fill each with spoonful of meat mixture.
Fold dough over.
Pinch and seal.
Brush a little water around edges before sealing.
Brush top with beaten egg.
Bake according to biscuit directions.

title: j.r.'s ozark fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together 3 times. Add to first mixture the flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add diced apples, vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: cheese ball
directions: Bring cheeses to room temperature.
Cream together until very creamy.
Add other ingredients except pecans.
Shape into a ball; roll in pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Simmer 1 to 3 hours.
One hour prior to eating time, add chopped okra and cooked chicken with chunks of fresh whitefish (optional).
About 20 minutes before serving, add peeled raw shrimp (medium).
May add shelled crab or clams or both.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet with Crisco. Combine butter flavor Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread raw hamburger in 8 x 8 x 3-inch dish.
Spread the soup over the meat.
(Do not dilute.)
Place frozen Tater Tots all over the top.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven about 45 minutes.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and cook on high until thick and transparent.
Let cool completely and add the food coloring and fold in the strawberries.
Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: penny stumler's beef ragout(french)
directions: Shake flour, salt, pepper and beef strips in a brown lunch bag. Brown beef in oil.
Add soup, 1 bay leaf, tomato paste and cinnamon.
Cook on low-medium (stir frequently) for at least 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Now, add carrots.
Cook another hour until meat and carrots are tender.
Serve over Mueller's made noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: honey mustard salad dressing
directions: Combine and add to salad.
If you use no-fat mayonnaise, it is a no-fat dressing.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine apple juice, cranberry juice, sugar, cinnamon sticks, cloves and lemon; simmer 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: bean bake
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion; drain.
Break up fried bacon and mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or put in crock-pot.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and place on bottom of casserole dish.
Top with chicken.
Mix undiluted soup, curry powder, lemon juice, and mayonnaise; spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
On the last 10 minutes top with grated cheese and then bread crumbs.

title: pasta and seafood salad
directions: Season pasta to taste.
Add mayonnaise to desired consistency and mix well.
Add peas, imitation crab meat and black olives; toss gently.
Chill and serve.

title: glorious macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Saute pimento and onion in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs and put into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.

title: hot cracker dip
directions: Mix together; put in pie pan.
On top, put 1/2 cup chopped pecans, sauteed in butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot with your choice of crackers.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Roll out dough to form a 14-inch circle.
Layer in order: Provolone cheese, pepperoni, Mozzarella cheese, broccoli, Colby cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bring sides of dough up and pinch to seal.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: okra casserole
directions: Fry bacon.
Remove from pan.
Chop onions and peppers.
Add to bacon drippings and cook until onions are golden.
Chop tomatoes and add to onions.
Cook, covered, 20 minutes over medium-low heat (until tender).
Add okra and cook until tender.

title: spaghetti with broccoli, tomato and roasted red peppers
directions: Cook spaghetti in sufficient boiling water for 3 minutes; add the broccoli.
Cook until spaghetti is al dente or firm to bite and the broccoli is tender, about 7 to 10 minutes.
Drain.

title: cheese and bacon puffs
directions: Mix ingredients; spread on party rye and broil until bubbly and brown.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Set aside.
Blend shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add flour to mixture.
Shape dough into balls and roll each in sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg mixture.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and mushrooms.
Drain off fat.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, mustard, ketchup and water.
Cover.
Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes or until liquid is reduced.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook zucchini and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese. Stir in vegetable mixture.
Separate dough into triangles. Place in ungreased 10-inch pie plate.
Press over bottom and up sides. Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture into crust.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with sliced apples.

title: sorry cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add biscuit mix, coconut and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan and cut in squares.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Beat	for
3 minutes. Pour in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Let stand for 5 minutes.	Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a blender.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Let cake cool before icing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up squash and onion.
Add salt and pepper and cover with water in a saucepan.
Cook 10 minutes.
Drain and mash like potatoes.
Add butter, egg, milk and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop scallop
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Trim excess fat from pork chops.
Rub skillet with fat trimmed from pork.
Brown pork in skillet; sprinkle with salt.
Heat water to boiling in 3-quart saucepan. Add carrots and frozen beans; heat to boiling.
Stir in butter, potato slices and sauce mix from scalloped potato package.
Mix soup, milk, basil and Worcestershire sauce; stir into vegetable mixture.
Pour into ungreased baking dish, 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inches.
Place pork on top.
Cover and bake 45 minutes. Uncover and bake until pork is tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable medley(serves 10)
directions: Partly cook carrot and celery in skillet with water.
Slice thin the onion and bell pepper.
Add beans, tomatoes, salt, sugar and tapioca.
Combine all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Stir half-way through baking.

title: crunchy caramel corn
directions: Melt caramels with water in saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Pour over combined popped popcorn and peanuts; toss until well coated.
Spread onto greased cookie sheet.
Let stand until set; break apart.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: baked cream of chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Cover with one can of chicken soup and 2 cans of water.
Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle paprika lightly over chicken.
Bake, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.
Turn chicken and stir.
Bake other side for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Debone it, in the same water you boiled the chicken.
Add both cans of soup, celery and the bell pepper.
Add the salt and pepper.
Roll out the canned biscuits in flour.
Cut the rolled out biscuits in small strips.
Drop the biscuits in the water and cook on low heat for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Boil milk and sugar until it forms a soft ball or 230° on candy thermometer.
Add dates and nuts; beat until creamy and very thick.
Put on wet towel.
Spread along short width of towel and roll up (log-style).
When cold, slice and serve.
Store in airtight container.
Very rich, especially if condensed milk is used.

title: old southern pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Mix in other ingredients. Pour into cake pans.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°, until done.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain corn, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to liquid to measure 1 cup.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk mixture and corn.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix until moistened.
Drop batter from tablespoon into deep fat at 375°. Fry until brown (3 to 4 minutes).
Makes 2 dozen.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Remove the jackets and slice (if small, leave whole). Place them in a baking dish and cover with a syrup made of other ingredients. Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour. Serve while hot.

title: butterfingers
directions: Cream soft margarine, powdered sugar, vanilla and salt. Gradually add flour and chopped nuts.
Roll dough in log shape and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Dust with powdered sugar when still warm.

title: fried catfish
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, salt, garlic salt, onion powder and pepper in paper bag.
Add fish, 3 to 4 at a time.
Shake to coat. Melt shortening in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add fish, 2 to 3 pieces at a time.
Cook for 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Remove.
Drain on paper towels.
Garnish with lemon.

title: honey poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.
Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix ingredients; drop by teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan to finish cooling on rack.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: picnic potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in the skins.
Cool, peel and dice.
Place in large bowl and add onion.
In medium saucepan, beat eggs; add sugar, flour, vinegar and water.
Boil to thicken.
Pour over warm potatoes; mix and cover.
Serve 15 minutes to 2 hours later.
This salad is best not refrigerated.

title: chicken and broccoli alfredo
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to package directions. Add broccoli for last 4 minutes of cooking time. Drain.

title: baked round steak
directions: Spread butter on steak.
Sprinkle mushrooms over steak.
Cover with soup mix.
Wrap in 2 thicknesses of foil.
Place in covered roaster with rack.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased tube and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 20 minutes in pan before taking out.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix and pour into floured and greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Put icing on while warm.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream the sugar, oleo, Crisco and egg yolks one at a time. Add milk and soda mixture alternately with flour.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Add pecans and coconut.
Bake in 3 layers using 9-inch greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Measure warm water into mixing bowl and stir in dry yeast. Heat milk and then stir in honey, salt, beaten eggs and shortening and add to yeast in bowl.
Add 1/2 of the flour and mix with a spoon or mixer until smooth.
Add enough of remaining flour to handle easily.
Turn onto lightly floured board, knead until smooth and elastic.
Put into a greased bowl, greased side up. Cover with damp cloth and let rise in a warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and let rise again until almost double, 30 to 45 minutes.
Shape rolls and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned corn bread
directions: Combine flour, meal and buttermilk.
(May need more buttermilk.)
Mix until you get light batter.
Pour into greased pan.
Cook approximately 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6.

title: bubble bread
directions: Spray a Bundt pan (or large tube pan) with Pam.
Dip each individual roll into the margarine and then roll in the cinnamon and sugar.
Place in baking pan.
Continue until all rolls have been rolled and placed in baking pan.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pepper steak
directions: Combine beef, pepper and onion.
Cook in gravy until tender. Serve over rice or noodles.
You can use leftovers.

title: french market soup mix
directions: Clean and wash the bean soup mix.
Place in a large pan. Cover with water to two-inches over the beans.
Soak overnight. Drain beans; add the 2-quarts water, ham hock, salt and pepper. Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for an additional 50 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove the ham hock from the soup and remove the meat from the bone.
Chop meat and return to the soup.

title: gold and green casserole
directions: Wash zucchini, slice off ends; slice into 1/4 pieces, boil in salted water, about 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash. Drain again; mix eggs, salt, pepper and onion.
Combine zucchini with egg mixture, corn and 1/2 the cheese.
Pour into oiled or greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Whisk soup and milk in a 2-quart bowl.
Add other ingredients. Refrigerate 6 to 12 hours or overnight.

title: linda's pumpkin crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin mixture.
Top with pecans.
Drizzle melted butter over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Serve chilled.
Top with whipped topping when served.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Combine and mix well.
Garnish with roasted slivered almonds. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chunky granola
directions: Place oats in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes, stirring 2 to 3 times.
Remove from oven and add sunflower seeds, coconut, wheat germ, powdered milk, cinnamon, slivered almonds.
Place honey and vegetable oil in a pan on stove top and heat until hot but not boiling.
Pour over dry mixture and stir until well coated.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, stirring every 3 to 5 minutes until uniformly golden brown.
Let cool in pan undisturbed, then break into chunks.
May add raisins, dates and dried apricots.
Store in airtight container.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits
in fourths.
Mix the cinnamon and 1 cup sugar together.
Shake cut biscuits into the sugar and cinnamon mixture. Grease tube pan.
Bring the brown sugar and margarine to a boil. Layer the tube pan with pieces of biscuits.
Pour syrup over all. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: 24 hour lettuce salad
directions: Break lettuce up into small pieces.
Do not cut or wash lettuce.
Must be dry as it is prepared.
Add in layers, the lettuce, chopped celery, onion and green pepper.
Add green peas, cooked in salted water, drained and cooled.
Do not add any other salt to salad.
Spread mayonnaise over top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Seal with Saran Wrap or cover seal if using the large Tupperware bowl.
Refrigerate for at least 8 hours before serving.
Toss just before serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water, let cool; then add strawberries, bananas and pineapple and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: coconut fruit squares
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 9-inch square pan.

title: day-care jiggles
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water or juice in a bowl.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Cut with any cookie cutter.

title: vanilla wafers
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Beat egg and add milk and vanilla.
Sift all dry ingredients alternately to creamed mixture.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Makes 82 (2-inch) cookies.

title: sue's pineapple cake
directions: Cake: Mix together cake mix, egg whites, oils, buttermilk, baking soda and 1/2 can pineapple with juice. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13 pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Flatten dinner rolls out on cookie sheet.
Put creases together. Bake according to directions until brown. Cool for 20 minutes.

title: gelatin punch cake
directions: Follow directions on cake box (use no cholesterol recipe if desired).
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix margarine and sugar well.
Add egg one at a time.
In separate bowl, mix flour, coconut, graham cracker crumbs, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with milk.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: party meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except for soup, and turn into loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then pour soup over loaf.
Bake 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Flour and salt pork chops; brown in oil.
Saute onion in butter.
Add mushrooms.
Place rice in casserole; top with onion and mushrooms.
Place pork chops on top.
Pour consomme and small amount of water over all. Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scones
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut the butter into the dry ingredients, using a pastry blender.
Add drained raisins to the flour mixture.
Use a fork and do not overmix.
It should take only a few turns to get a dough.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix with electric mixer; beat all ingredients well.
Pour into crust; refrigerate.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: the best lithuanian potato pancakes
directions: After draining potatoes, let water stand, then when water is poured off, return starch from container bottom to grated potatoes.
After everything is mixed, spoon into hot grease and fry until golden brown.

title: diabetic breakfast - spanish omelet
directions: Break egg and beat until yellow and thick.
Add water, chopped onion, chopped green pepper, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in a small frying pan and pour in mixture.
Cook slowly over low flame until golden brown.

title: simple "microwave" fudge
directions: In a large bowl, place sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Heat in microwave for two minutes or until butter is melted.
Remove from microwave; add nuts if desired.
With a wooden spoon, beat until mixture is smooth.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool and enjoy.

title: curry lentils and rice
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic in oil for 2 to 3 minutes. Add rice and stir until rice is coated.
Add mustard and stir. Add rest of ingredients, except water.
Stir; add water.
Simmer about 2 hours, check water level occasionally; add more water if mixture is too thick.
Simmer longer if too watery.

title: eggplant with tomato sauce
directions: Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Sprinkle with salt. Place in a deep dish; cover and let stand for 30 minutes.
Rinse with cold water; drain and let dry on paper towels.
In a 2-quart saucepan, heat olive oil over medium.
Add tomatoes, garlic, basil and sugar; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 45 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Season with salt and pepper.
Keep warm while preparing eggplant.
In a large skillet, heat about 1/4 cup oil; brown eggplant, a quarter at a time, adding more oil as needed. Place on a serving platter one row at a time.
Cover with sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Serve warm.
Yields 8 servings.

title: breast of chicken veronique
directions: Cook chicken breasts in saucepan.
Salt and pepper.
Place chicken breasts in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.

title: jean's chicken casserole
directions: Chop chicken. Cook rice in broth. Mix all ingredients and sprinkle with parsley. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 16.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 1-quart size casserole in oven.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour batter into melted margarine.
Spoon fruit over top.
Use either small can of sliced fruit with syrup or fresh fruit with water and sugar added to make 2 cups.
Add spice to fruit, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: carrot and onion relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium size bowl. Stir well and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, remove bay leaf and drain off liquid.
Goes very well with grilled poultry or pork.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Bring
syrup
to
a
boil, then remove and add coconut. Let cool
and make into balls.
Dip in melted chocolate.
You can also make Mounds and Almond Joys with this.

title: french fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel
and rinse
the
potatoes;
cut
into
small
thin strips longwise; dry.
In the hot cooking oil in a frypan, fry the potatoes as French fried white potatoes, 3 to 5 minutes or until a golden
brown.
Remove
and
drain
on
paper
towels. Sprinkle salt over the potatoes and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add eggs to sugar and shortening mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Cut into desired shapes. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar or spread with vanilla icing.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oranges, eggs and oil.
Beat 2 minutes on high, then 1 minute on low.
Pour into three 9-inch greased, floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from a pan and cool completely.

title: baked onions
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange the onions in a greased baking dish.
Dot with butter or oil and bake until nearly charred, tinged with black and brown, for 45 minutes to 1 hour and 15 minutes, adding more butter or oil as necessary to keep moist.
Salt and pepper.
Serve hot or chilled.

title: tunky's caraway bread
directions: Soften	butter.
Place	1
loaf
of French bread in the freezer.
When
frozen,
slice
outside crust off entire loaf. Then
slice bread, but not completely through.
Butter slices, then ice
entire loaf and bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Do
not
put loaf in foil.
Time of preparation: 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fried tofu in mushroom sauce
directions: Cut tofu into 1 x 1 x 1/4-inch slices.
Add flour, 1 teaspoon water and salt to egg.
Beat until smooth.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Dip curd slices in the batter and brown on both sides in hot oil.
Remove browned curd slices to a dish.
Brown mushrooms, sliced, lightly in leftover oil.
Add water and bouillon and bring to a boil.
Add soy sauce.
Mix cornstarch and 1/4 cup water. Stir into sauce and cook until thick.
Add browned curd slices to sauce.
Cover pan and simmer for 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve at once. Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
30 minutes.

title: vodka sauce
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Add crushed tomatoes and cook until heated.
Stir in vodka and cook 30 minutes.
Slowly add heavy cream while stirring.
Simmer 10 minutes and add pepper and salt to taste.
Serve over pasta.

title: crunch top potatoes
directions: Melt butter in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan at 325°.
Add single layer of potatoes.
Turn them once to butter both sides.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over top of potatoes and bake 1/2 hour at 350° or until done and tops are crispy.
Serve hot.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread pineapple evenly over bottom and into the corners of pan.
Cover with pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Top with nuts.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: green chile hominy
directions: Saute the onions in a little of the bacon drippings and put aside.
Heat the hominy in a separate saute pan, stirring often. When heated thoroughly, add the hominy liquid and jalapeno juice, bring back to high temperature and add 3/4 of the cheese.
When the cheese melts, add half the peppers, chilies and bacon and all the onion.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and sprinkle with the remaining cheese, bacon, chilies and peppers.
(At this point it can be refrigerated or even frozen, if you want to make it in advance.)
Bake at 325° until cheese on top melts, about 15 minutes (or 40 minutes, if refrigerated).

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Mix soup and broth, bring to a boil, pour over chicken.
Combine flour, buttermilk, melted margarine and pepper.
Spoon over chicken. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Combine coconut and butter or margarine; press into 8-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° until coconut is golden, about 10 minutes. Cool thoroughly.
In small saucepan, dissolve coffee powder in 2 tablespoons water; add chocolate bar.
Stir chocolate mixture over low heat until melted; cool.
Fold in whipped dessert topping; pile into coconut crust.
Chill in freezer several hours or overnight.
(It will not freeze solid.)

title: greek style orzo with tomatoes and spinach
directions: Coarsely chop tomatoes and set aside.
Cook orzo according to package directions.
Set aside.
In large skillet, brown onion and garlic slightly in oil.
Stir in chicken broth, orzo, seasonings and tomatoes.
Stir in spinach and cheese.
Cook about 3 minutes, if serving immediately, or put all into baking dish and finish in 350° oven just until thoroughly hot.
If doubled, this nicely fills a 9 x 13-inch pan and serves a crowd.
Great with roast or grilled meats.

title: zesty breaded chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then soup mix and bread crumbs (combined).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, arrange chicken; drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake 20 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the sugar and milk until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Take from heat. Add other ingredients.
Beat until cool. Pour into greased pan and cut into squares.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients (optional) or mix together.
Add to first mixture. Fold in pecans and apples.
Bake in a 13 x 8-inch greased pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine and refrigerate overnight.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press ground beef in bottom of long dish.
Sprinkle bell pepper and onion over, layer cheese over and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread Tater Tots over casserole, then spread soup from cans over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots.
Simmer onion and celery in butter.
Make white sauce by combining milk and flour; heat until sauce thickens.
Add onion and celery to white sauce.
Layer carrots and Cheddar cheese in casserole dish.
Cover with white sauce.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cup salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail and dry pudding mix together.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
(Lite fruit cocktail and sugar-free pudding mix can be used.)
You can use bananas and a bit of other canned fruit.
Also good with French vanilla, banana or pistachio puddings.

title: fluffy potato casserole
directions: Beat potatoes with electric mixer.
Add cheese, onion, flour, salt and pepper.
Beat at medium speed until blended, then at high speed until light and fluffy.
Spoon into a 9-inch baking dish (1 1/2-quart).
Put onion rings on top just before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 35 minutes.
Cover the last 10 minutes.

title: extra easy lasagna
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and drain fat. Add spaghetti sauce. Heat through, stirring occasionally.

In a 2-quart oblong baking dish, spread 1 1/2 cups meat mixture. Top with 3 uncooked lasagna noodles, half of the Ricotta cheese and half of the Mozzarella. Repeat layers. Top with remaining meat mixture. Slowly pour water around inside edges of baking dish. Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat after each egg.
Add flour, beat until smooth.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and almond extracts. Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 55 minutes or until pie is set.

title: gina's vegetable casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and spread in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with Cheez Its and Cheddar.
Drizzle melted butter over entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Blend together thoroughly and put in a 3 pound container to store.
To use, mix 1/3 cup of the mix and 1 cup hot water.
Makes approximately 50 cups.

title: strawberry sheet cake
directions: Place cake mix in large mixing bowl.
Measure 1/2 cup strawberries and add enough water to measure 1 cup.
Add to cake mix.
Add oil.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add jello and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° until top springs back lightly.

title: old-fashioned meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except ketchup.
Mix well and place on drip pan.
Roasting pans will do if grease is drained every 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread ketchup thoroughly over top and bake for 15 minutes.

title: parmesan fillets(weight watchers)
directions: Preheat broiler.
In cup, combine oil and lemon juice.
Dip fish in combination.
Place on cookie sheet and sprinkle cheese on top.
Broil until golden brown and fish flakes easily.
Makes 1 serving with 162 calories.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Place cheeses and mushrooms in bottom of pie shell.
Beat eggs, cream and seasonings.
Pour egg mixture into shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Moisten bread crumbs with hot meat stock.
Add salt, pepper, sage and eggs.
Melt butter.
Simmer chopped celery and onion slightly and add to the dressing.
Then add boiled eggs and giblets if desired.

title: maggie's award winning molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add molasses.
Add soda to boiling water and add to mixture.
Add the dry ingredients.
Roll out, sprinkle sugar over the dough.
Cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Add milk, soda, salt, sugar and all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into hot, greased pan.
Bake at 400° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Arrange pecans in pan; dot with butter.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Take out and salt.
Let cool.
Can be frozen.

title: spaghetti(with spicy peanut chicken and vegetables)
directions: About 40
minutes
before
serving prepare spaghetti as label directs.
Meanwhile
in
5 quart Dutch oven or saucepot over
high heat
in 2 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook chicken and
all
but 1
tablespoon green onion, stirring quickly and constantly until chicken is lightly browned and just loses its pink	color,	about 5
minutes.
With
slotted	spoon, remove chicken mixture to bowl and keep warm.

title: hash brown supreme
directions: Brown ground beef and drain excess grease off.
Combine the ground beef with the next 8 ingredients.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine the cornflakes and melted butter.
Sprinkle the mixture on top of the other ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: baked potato sauce
directions: Beat all ingredients together with a mixer.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water, salt and peanuts until mixture spins a thread. Remove from heat. Add food color and vanilla. Beat until starts to get thick. Pour on waxed paper. Let cool and break into pieces.

title: honey of a fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter; add cornstarch and cocoa.
Blend well.
Add honey and water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve over ice cream.
Can be served warm or cold.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: super cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cabbage, until dissolved.
Add cabbage and toss well.
Marinate until chilled.
Drain before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: five-flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool on wire rack.
Spoon hot glaze over warm cake.
Cool.

title: fruit salad sauce
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour.
Add egg and stir.
Add orange juice and cook in double boiler until thickened.
Delicious on fresh fruit salad or plain cake.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in dry place.
When you want a cup of hot chocolate fill cup up halfway with mixture and add hot water.
Stir.
Add marshmallows if desired.

title: italian turkey stew
directions: Bring 3 cups of low-sodium chicken broth and 1 cup of tomato juice to a boil in a large pot.
Add 3/4 pound of turkey tenders, cut into 1/2-inch strips and reduce heat to medium.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove turkey and reserve in a separate bowl.
Add handful of cauliflower florets; stir and cover for 5 minutes.
Add handful of broccoli flowerets, plum tomatoes, mushrooms, onion, frozen gnocchi pasta, garlic and a couple shakes of dried oregano.
Cover and cook 10 minutes, stirring often.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir together apples, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Place apple mixture in greased pan.
Mix up white cake mix according to box directions.
Pour batter over apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until cake springs back when touched.
Invert onto cake plate when removed from oven.
Cool to serve.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Place carrots in large saucepan with 1-inch boiling water. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add onions.
Cover and cook 5 minutes longer or until vegetables are just tender.
Drain. Return vegetables to saucepan.
Add margarine, brown sugar, ginger and salt.
Stirring frequently, cook over medium-high heat 5 minutes or until vegetables are glazed.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Combine dry ingredients well. Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned but still soft at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and water.
Boil (without stirring) to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Pour slowly 1/2 of syrup (putting rest back on fire) beating constantly over stiffly beaten egg whites for 2 minutes.
Pour other half in slowly.
Beat until mixture cools and holds shape.
Add nuts; stir by hand.
Drop on wax paper.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes according to package directions.
Stir in sour cream, chives and bacon bits.
Spoon into 1-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: sunday sweet potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Pour into greased 9 x 11-inch or 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add flour and baking powder and beat until smooth.
Add eggs.
Beat until combined.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake an additional 45 minutes or until set.

title: ellen titus' marinade
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over meat.
London broil or any meat you wish to flavor.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 3 to 4 hours, turning every few hours.
Baste meat with marinade while cooking.
Add any other seasoning you like to season meat with.

title: quick and easy party meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs and soup mix real good. Roll into 1-inch balls. Cook at 350° until brown.

While meat balls are cooking, in a large saucepan, mix chili sauce and jelly, heating to boiling. When meat balls are cooked, add them to the sauce. Cover and simmer on warm heat until ready to serve. The meat balls can be made ahead of time and placed in the freezer until you want to have a party.

title: sweet-n-sour meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and form into small balls. Place in baking dish or crock-pot.
Combine other ingredients together and pour over meatballs.
Bake at 375° or in crock-pot on high until done.

title: norwegian meatballs
directions: Saute the onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix all the above ingredients and shape into balls. Brown on both sides.
Place meatballs in a casserole.

title: spanish rice ajo style
directions: Saute onion. Add rice and lightly saute.
Add water, bouillon cubes, garlic and stewed tomatoes. Cook until tender and thickened.
Yummy.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Combine cucumber, onion and salt and let stand, lightly covered, for at least 2 hours, then drain.
Place ingredients in a bowl and add sour cream, vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Fold into cucumber mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.
Best if made a day ahead.
Goes well with chicken, beef or pork.

title: chow - chow
directions: After chopping all vegetables, combine in large pan on stove. Add white vinegar and salt.
You may dilute vinegar with some water.
Heat until vegetables are heated through.
Pack hot in jars.
Seal at once.

title: chicken breast in herbs
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over cooked chicken.
Bake 325° for 50 minutes uncovered.

title: chocolate icebox cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water (double boiler).
Mix beaten egg yolks and sugar together. Beat into chocolate until sugar is dissolved, then allow to cool. Beat egg whites stiff.
Beat egg whites into chocolate mixture. Whip 1/2 pint heavy cream and add to mixture. Alternate ladyfingers (split) and chocolate mixture in a deep dish cake pan. Chill for 24 hours.
Serve with light topping of whipping cream.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar, then sprinkle sugar over top. Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours. Mix well and enjoy.

title: peanut butter log
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until it becomes hard ball stage.
Beat egg whites in large bowl until stiff.
Pour sugar mixture into bowl with whites while still beating.
Continue to beat until real thick, like a dough.
Spread out on waxed paper.
Make a thin layer.
Spread peanut butter all over; roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut and serve.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding mix, milk and vanilla until thickened. Combine sour cream and sugar. Stir into pudding mixture. Fold in Cool Whip until well blended. Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mixture alternating in 9 X 13 dish. Chill. Serves 6-8.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash and dry apples, oranges and cranberries.
Cut apples into squares; remove core and pare.
Remove all white membrane and seeds; section oranges over bowl to preserve juice.
Put oranges, apples and cranberries through food chopper.
Add sugar and juice from oranges; mix well.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: fruit and bran muffins
directions: Combine the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl.
Mix the cereal and milk together in a large mixing bowl; let stand for 3 minutes.
Add the egg and oil to the cereal-milk mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add the dry ingredients; stir.
Fill each of 12 paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Simmer vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard and celery seed for 5 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers and onions and put in refrigerator. Let set 7 days before eating.
(If you want crisper pickles, soak cucumbers
first overnight in 1/2 cup lime and water to cover. Rinse well, then follow recipe.)

title: spooky sandwich
directions: Cut jack-o-lantern faces in one slice of bread.
Spread second slice with butter or mayonnaise.
Lay on slice of cheese.
Top with jack-o-lantern slice.
Serve plain or toast.

title: broccoli 'n cheese stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Between waxed paper, pound each breast 1/4 inch thick and season; set aside.
In medium skillet over medium heat, saute onion and broccoli in hot butter for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in 1 cup cheese and nutmeg.
Place equal amount of cheese-broccoli mixture in center of each breast.
Fold in edges to cover stuffing.
Place seam side down in lightly greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining broccoli mixture, cheese and paprika.
Bake until chicken is cooked and filling is hot, about 12-25 minutes.
Serves 4 - 5.

title: black walnut fudge
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sugar, margarine, milk and syrup in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Stop stirring and continue heating until mixture reaches soft ball stage, 234° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and stir in white chocolate chips until melted; add Marshmallow Creme, walnuts and vanilla, beating well after each addition.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cool completely, cut into squares.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Place berries in dish. Sprinkle 1/2 of the sugar over the berries.
Mix the other 1/2 of the sugar with flour and butter. Mix until crumbly. Spread over berries and bake at 350° until brown and crisp.

title: creamy penne pasta
directions: Boil pasta.
Drain and keep warm.
Heat remaining ingredients in saucepan to low boil.
Serve over pasta.
Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all
ingredients except 1 cup of nuts.
Form into a ball. Roll in reserved nuts.
Chill.

title: pickled crabs
directions: Boil crabs as usual with salt, pepper, bay leaves, lemon, a few cloves (whole) and crab boil.
Clean crabs by removing backs and inedible parts.
Break in half and remove claws.
Put crab halves and claws into a gallon glass jar.
Combine lemon (rind, too), onions, celery, oil and vinegar in a blender.
Blend together. Pour mixture over crabs.
Let stand overnight to coat and season. Shake occasionally.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Beat approximately 3 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into three 8-inch round pans.
Bake at 325° for approximately 40 minutes or until done.
Top with Watergate Cake Icing.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix refried beans and taco seasoning together in a small bowl.
Spread in a 9x13 inch pan.
Then in following order add onion, sour cream, picante sauce, lettuce, tomatoes, black olives, and top with shredded cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil white sugar, brown sugar, orange juice, margarine and cornstarch until thick.
Pour sauce over potatoes and cook 30 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: broccoli and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and macaroni according to directions on packages.
Cut broccoli into bite size pieces; mix with macaroni in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a saucepan, prepare soup as directed on cans, using milk.
Add 3/4 of grated cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Pour over broccoli and macaroni and mix thoroughly. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes until brown and bubbly.
Be sure pan is large enough as it tends to bubble over.
Serves a crowd.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add blueberries and 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Add pineapple.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set.
Spray pan with cooking spray.
Whip cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread on top of jello.
Top with nuts.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Cook until thickened.
Thin with milk or cream.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tiramisu
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with ladyfingers, cut side up.
Sprinkle with liqueur.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Stir in about 1/4 of the whipped cream to lighten the mixture, then fold in the remaining whipped cream.
Pour into ladyfinger lined pan.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Sprinkle top lightly with unsweetened cocoa.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Melt butter.
Add flour and brown. Add chicken broth and cook until thick.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour mixture over chicken and top with pie shell.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add 2 cups milk.
Heat remainder of milk in a double boiler to just below boiling temperature.
Add the egg mixture and continue cooking 30 minutes, stirring constantly.
Strain.
If custard curdles beat with a mixer.
Chill.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Add whole milk.
Put strawberries in blender and blend.
Add to mixture and put in ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: new potatoes fried whole
directions: Do not peel the potatoes.
Wash potatoes with a vegetable brush to remove the skin.
Place in a large iron skillet in which you have already heated the bacon grease. Salt and pepper to taste. Fry until golden brown on all sides and potatoes are tender.
Use medium heat, about 20 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In large saucepan, or Dutch oven, combine beef shank, water, salt, pepper, bay leaf and garlic.
Bring to boil.
Simmer, covered, 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove beef from soup and separate from bone; return to soup.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: *baked spinach
directions: Combine spinach, eggs, cheese, milk and onion.
Put into buttered baking dish.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top of the spinach mixture.
(I butter bread slices and cube; can vary seasoning by sprinkling on top poultry seasoning, garlic, etc.) Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mushroom swiss steak
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place meat on 2 sheets heavy-duty foil and sprinkle both sides with mushroom mix.
Wrap loosely in foil; seal in edges airtight with double foil.
Place in shallow baking pan and bake for 1 hour or until fork-tender.

title: apple pizza
directions: Combine flour, salt and shortening.
Add yolk. Mix lightly. Roll out half to fill jelly roll pan.
Save half for top. Sprinkle bottom with oatmeal.
Arrange sliced apples on this. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Roll out top crust and fit over bottom, crimping the edges. Beat egg whites lightly. Spread on top crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Grease 11 x 7 baking dish.
Cook shells and drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Melt 2 T butter, add celery and onion.
Cook for 7 minutes stirring often till soft.
Add garlic and cook 2 minutes. Remove 3/4 cup cooked vegetables to large bowl.
Add 2 T butter to skillet, melt and add flour stirring for 30 seconds.
Gradually stir in milk and broth for white sauce.
Then, add mustard, salt, thyme, parsley and pepper. Cook, stirring often, for 5 minutes till thickened and boils. Remove from heat.
Add turkey to veggies in a large bowl.
Stir in mayo and 1/2 cup white sauce.
Add raisins and 1/3 cup nuts.
Fill each shell with 3 T each of turkey mixture.
Spoon remaining sauce over filled shells in baking dish. Bake 20 minutes at 375 F till heated through.

title: boiled-fried potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice into 1-inch thick pieces.
Boil until potatoes begin to turn tender; drain.
Melt the butter over medium heat in skillet.
Place potatoes in skillet with salt and pepper. Fry until golden brown.

title: baklava 1
directions: Combine coarsely ground walnuts with sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Line bottom of buttered pan, 9 x 12-inch, with 10 to 12 fila, brushing each with melted butter.
Sprinkle with thin layer of nut mixture.
Cover with 3 fila, brushing each with melted butter.
Sprinkle with more nut mixture.
Repeat process, until all nut mixture is used, usually in 4 layers.
Cover with remaining buttered fila.
Chill 25 minutes.
Cut pastry into small diamond shapes.
Brush again with melted butter.
Insert whole cloves in center of each piece.
Bake in slow oven, 325°, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
When slightly browned, remove from oven; slowly pour enough cooled syrup over hot Baklava until completely absorbed.

title: cheesy tomato bake
directions: Cook noodles as per instructions, removing from water while slightly firm.
Prepare tomato soup with 1 can milk (skim is fine) for each can of soup.
Bring to boil, remove from heat.
Mix soup and noodles.
Cut cheese into small pieces and add to mixture. Cover with slices of cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° or until cheese bubbles.
Serve hot.

title: sweet and sour sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, eggs and bread crumbs.
Using palm of hands, shape mixture into balls the size of walnuts.
Saute in skillet until browned on all sides; drain.
Combine catsup, brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce; pour over sausage balls.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot in chafing dish.
If made ahead, refrigerate or freeze balls in their sauce.
To serve, reheat in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: date squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix margarine, sugar and eggs well.
Stir in Bisquick, nuts and dates. Spread in pan, using hands to press dough.
Bake 25 minutes. Cool 1 hour and cut in squares.

title: pastry wrapped pears with caramel sauce
directions: Peel pears, leaving stems intact.
Cut each in half crosswise just above the thickest part of the pear; remove core with a melon-ball scoop or a small spoon, being careful not to break through the bottom of pear.
Fill cavity with chocolate pieces; replace top.
Thaw pastry 20 minutes; unfold and roll each sheet on a lightly floured surface to a 10 x 13-inch rectangle.
Cut 6 squares from pastry, each about 3 1/3 x 3 1/3-inch.
Cut remaining pastry lengthwise into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Brush strips lightly with egg mixture.
Place a pear in the center of each pastry square and bring edges up.
Brush outside with egg mixture. Starting at bottom, wrap pears with pastry strips, egg-washed side out, overlapping slightly as you go up the pear.
Leave stem exposed at top.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 375° and bake 5 minutes longer or until pastry is puffed and golden brown.
Serve pears with Caramel Sauce.

title: witches brew
directions: Cook all ingredients together for 15 minutes.
Great for Halloween, Thanksgiving, Christmas Eve, showers, anytime.

title: hawaiian fruit salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a pan.
Gradually add in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add lemon juice; cool to room temperature.
Cook pasta in 3 quarts water, oil and rest of salt (2 teaspoons).
Cool to room temperature.
Combine and let set overnight in an airtight container in refrigerator.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.

title: fruit cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg into large bowl.
Add pecans, candied pineapple, candied cherries and raisins.
Mix until fruit and nuts are well coated with dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well after each egg.
Add flavoring.
Add to fruit mixture.
Mix well to combine. Bake in a 10-inch tube pan at 270° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
About 1/2 hour before cake is done, brush top with honey or light corn syrup. Decorate with fruit and nuts.
Return cake to oven to finish baking.

title: southwest chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with cumin, chili powder, salt and pepper. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet.
Add chicken.
Cook until no longer pink.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and picante.
Cover and cook until chicken is tender.
Rice may be cooked in this or separately with the gravy served over.
Add cheese if rice is cooked with chicken.

title: zucchini peanut cake
directions: Cream
oil, sugar and eggs together in large bowl.
Add grated zucchini.
In another large bowl mix all other ingredients.
Add first
mixture
to	flour,	mixing	well.
Do
not overstir.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Crush vanilla wafers and add alternately with milk. Add coconut and chopped pecans.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350°
for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
This cake does not rise very much.

title: super sausage balls
directions: Mix together and roll into walnut size balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken florentine with lemon-mustard sauce(makes 4 servings)
directions: Cook spinach and drain. Pound chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness. Pour Egg Beaters into shallow bowl. Combine bread crumbs, basil and garlic. Dip chicken breasts into Egg Beaters, then coat with bread crumb mixture. In a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, melt 1 tablespoon spread. Add chicken; cook for 5 to 7 minutes on each side or until browned and no longer pink in center. Remove chicken from skillet; keep warm. In same skillet, melt remaining spread; stir in water, mustard, lemon juice and sugar. Simmer 1 minute or until thickened.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all together.
Store in Tupperware Econo canister.
Mix 4 heaping tablespoonfuls to 1 cup of water.

title: chicken-mac casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In saucepan, plate hot macaroni, bacon, chicken and 1/2 can onions.
In medium bowl, combine soup, sour cream, spinach, garlic powder and 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Spoon half macaroni mixture into greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover with half spinach mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, for 3 to 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend pudding in milk with wire whisk. Add sour cream and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Mix well; set aside.
In large bowl, alternate cookies, bananas and pudding mix in layers. Top with reserved Cool Whip and banana slices.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 16.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 pan with Pam.
Cook apple wedges in microwave for 2 minutes.
Wrap each wedge in a crescent roll.
Place in pan. Melt butter and add sugar, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour over crescent rolls.
Top with can of Mountain Dew.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In casserole, layer sliced summer squash, zucchini, tomatoes, green peppers and onions.
Between layers, sprinkle Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Dot with butter.
Top with crushed potato chips and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan(oven baked)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Dip chicken in egg, then bread crumbs, coating well.

title: sausage rounds
directions: Brown meats.
Add cheese and cook until it melts.
Add seasonings and mushrooms; mix thoroughly.
Spread on slices of party bread.
Place on a baking sheet and broil until bubbly and browned.
May be frozen after they are broiled.
Makes 15 slices; 289 calories per slice.

title: tiramisu
directions: Whip the cream until firm and place in refrigerator.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar and continue beating until stiff.
Refrigerate.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine egg, 1/4 cup of the tomato soup and next 5 ingredients. Add beef and mix well.
Shape into 20 meatballs.
Place in skillet. Mix remaining soup, 1/2 cup water and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Bring to boiling and reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 40 minutes, stirring often.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast
in
milk.
Add
sugar,
salt and cooled butter.
Mix well.
Add
flour
and
mix well.
Let rise until almost double in
bulk.
Punch down.
Turn onto floured board. Roll
to
1/4-inch
thickness.
Cut
into 2-inch round pieces. Dip each piece in melted butter.
Place in Bundt pan, overlapping each piece.
Stack
in pan until all dough is used.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes until golden brown. Do not slice. Just tear off.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Microwave the cream cheese, shrimp broth (drained from can of shrimp), Worcestershire sauce and onions.
Mix in shrimp.

title: pork tenderloin with raspberry sauce supreme
directions: With flat side of wide knife, press each pork tenderloin slice to 1-inch thickness.
Lightly sprinkle both sides of each slice with cayenne pepper.
Heat butter in nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add pork slices; cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side.

title: margie thomason's lemon-buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and beat.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together, alternately with buttermilk.
Add flavorings.
Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli jennifer
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 1-quart casserole.
Combine broccoli, soup, mayonnaise, cheese, onion and egg and blend well. Turn into prepared dish.
Sprinkle with crackers and dot with butter.
Bake about 35 minutes until bubbly and heated through.

title: crab spread
directions: Soften cheese and mix with crab meat and seafood seasoning. Make into a ball and place on serving dish.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, milk and butter.
Pour 1/2 batter into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes at 350°.
Batter will puff up, but will still be gooey.

title: fresh blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix 8 tablespoons of butter and 1/2 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Batter will be stiff.
In a large bowl, gently toss berries with remaining sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Pour into buttered 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Dot with remaining butter. Spoon batter over top of berries, covering them as much as possible.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until pastry is light brown.
Serve with ice cream.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Grease 9-inch pie pan. Melt butter and blend with sugar and egg. Mix dry ingredients in and add apples and pecans. Spread in pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with confectioners sugar glaze or ice cream.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 300°F for 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon into muffin pan.
Bake at 370° until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Blanch the broccoli for 5 minutes, then dip in cold water and drain.
Toss all of the ingredients together and let sit overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat soup, milk, butter and onion.
Pour over 1 C. croutons and the chicken.

title: the original chex party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°. Melt butter in large roasting pan in oven. Stir in seasonings. Gradually stir in remaining ingredients until evenly coated. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on paper towels to cool. Store in airtight container. Makes 12 cups snack.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: Place the apples into a greased 6 x 9-inch oblong baking dish. In a mixing bowl, sift the flour; add baking powder, sugar and salt.
Mix an egg into these dry ingredients until crumbly.
Pour the crumbly mixture evenly on top of apples.
Pour the melted margarine evenly over the dry crumbs.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes (until golden brown).

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Blend all the ingredients, except the steak.
Pour mixture over the steak and let marinate for 4 or 5 hours.
Turn occasionally.
Grill over a high flame for about 10 minutes, turning once.

title: fresh salsa
directions: In a large bowl combine the tomatoes, scallions, garlic, cilantro and lime juice.
If the tomatoes are not very juicy, gradually stir in up to 1/4 cup of cold water to moisten the mixture.
Stir in the chilies and oregano; season with salt.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread pineapple over pie filling, juice and all.
Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple. Melt margarine or butter.
Pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut and chopped nuts over top. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll chipped beef into roll and slice across, making narrow strips.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
(Use your hands to thoroughly mix it.)
Form into a ball and roll in pecans if so desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken bow tie pasta
directions: Cook chicken chunks in olive oil. Add rest of ingredients except olives and tomatoes and saute until green peppers are done, approx. 5 minutes. Then add tomatoes and olives, cook until hot, 5-10 minutes. Pour mixture over 1 pkg. of cooked bow tie pasta. Top with fresh parmesan cheese.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: t-bone rosemary
directions: Mix a marinade with the olive oil, black pepper, parsley, rosemary and garlic.
Place steaks in glass container and pour marinade over them.
Marinate for at least 1 hour.
Grill over hot fire for 4 to 5 minutes a side.
Turn the steak and brush marinade on browned side.
Sprinkle lightly with salt before serving. Serves 4.

title: friday night carrot pancakes*
directions: Brown onion in 2 tablespoons oil in medium frying pan.
Add onion to carrots, egg, matzo meal and seasonings.
Shape into 4 pancakes and brown on each side with remaining oil.
Great with chicken or for Passover.

title: microwave quick beef pie
directions: In plastic colander, crumble beef.
Add onion.
Microwave on High for 6 to 7 minutes (stirring halfway through).
Drain fat. Add soup, salt and pepper; mix well.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes.
Drop potatoes in mounds around edge of bowl.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Let set for 5 minutes before serving.

title: javaneese dinner
directions: Serves about 14 people.
Dishes of each ingredient are placed around table and each person goes down the line adding each thing on top of the other with hot gravy last.
Be sure they don't start out with too large a serving of rice.

title: oranges grand marnier
directions: Get a 1/2-inch slice from the stem end of each orange.
Scoop out pulp, removing membrane and seeds; reserve orange shells.
Chop pulp, and drain well.
Combine pulp, Grand Marnier and sherbet; stir until blended.
Spoon mixture into orange shells, and place in muffin pans.
Freeze 8 hours.
Remove from freezer 20 to 30 minutes before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: the world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugars until fluffy. Add egg and mix well.
Add oil and vanilla, mixing well.
Add oats, corn flakes, coconut and nuts, stirring well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for a few minutes before removing.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Combine egg, onion, soup and mayonnaise in a small bowl.
Place layer of broccoli in a one-quart casserole.
Add layer of cheese.
Pour a small amount of sauce over cheese.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Top with stuffing mix.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Place first four dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Separate yolks and whites of eggs into separate bowls.
Beat egg yolks well, then add melted butter or oil.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients.
Combine with a few swift strokes.
The batter will have a pebbled look.
Beat until stiff, but not dry.
Add the three egg whites and fold into batter until barely blended.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press dough into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish to form crust. Brown sausage and drain.
Spoon over crust.
Sprinkle hash browns and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper in mixer bowl.
Pour over potato layer.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° until crust is golden brown and eggs are set.
Serve warm.

title: raisin-peanut bars
directions: Microwave peanut butter, sugar and syrup for 2 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Add in remaining ingredients.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Store airtight.

title: no flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Put on cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio bundt cake
directions: Mix
all ingredients together with beater until blended well. Butter
Bundt pan.	Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until top is brown, at 350°.

title: chicken scampi
directions: In a large frying pan,
melt down margarine and add the finely chopped garlic;
keep on
low
so they don't get brown. Add the chopped parsley and
then
put the chicken in the pan. Cook this for 20 to 25
minutes.
You could add a little white pepper and 2 tablespoons of white
wine.
(I
usually
add the white pepper and the white wine, I think it tastes better.)

title: sunday steaks
directions: Dredge steaks with flour and pepper; brown lightly in hot oil. Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with dry soup mix.
Add mushrooms and liquid; top with sliced onion.
Mix gravy and water; pour over all.
Cover and bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: tops' cornbread dressing
directions: Brown pork in skillet, approximately 10 minutes.
Mix ground meat with pork and cook an additional 10 minutes.
Add onions and celery to meat mixture and saute 15 minutes.
Add soup and broth to meat mixture and heat thoroughly.
Check seasonings.
This can be spicy because you will add the cornbread to it.
Remove from heat and add the crumbled cornbread.
Add chopped green onions and chopped fresh parsley.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Combine corn syrup, brown sugar, salt, butter and vanilla in a bowl. Add eggs; mix well. Stir in walnuts.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: chicken squares
directions: Combine chicken, rice and celery.
Beat eggs, seasoning and broth; mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Fill a salad bowl half full with torn lettuce leaves. Chop some celery and put a layer on top of lettuce. Next put a layer of chopped green pepper. Slice and separate the red onion into rings and put on a layer of onion rings. Cook some frozen peas till they are just barely tender (about 4 minutes). Drain and add peas as next layer. Next add a layer of cauliflower florets. Now spread a layer of mayonnaise. Be sure to spread the mayo and seal it to the edges of bowl. Sprinkle 2 Tbsp of sugar over the mayo. Sprinkle parmesan cheese
and crumbled bacon on top. cover and chill overnight.

title: coconut marshmallow nests
directions: Combine water and food color in small bowl or small jar with cover or resealable plastic bag.
