Add coconut; toss with fork or shake closed jar or plastic bag until coconut is evenly coated. Microwave marshmallows and butter in medium microwave-safe bowl 30 seconds at HIGH (100%); stir. If necessary, microwave an additional 15 seconds at a time, stirring after each heating, until mixture is melted and smooth when stirred. Stir in tinted coconut. Line tray or cookie sheet with wax paper. Drop coconut mixture in 12 equal mounds onto prepared tray. Shape coconut mounds with moistened fingers into small nest shapes. Cool completely. Allow to air dry until slightly hardened. Fill with milk chocolate eggs. Makes 12 candies.

title: red rice
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter or margarine and olive oil until soft in medium saucepan.
Stir in rice, tomatoes, chicken broth, salt and pepper; heat to boiling, cover, turn down to low. Cook slowly 15 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Fluff up rice with fork, spoon into a serving bowl.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Pierce hash browns package.
Cook the potatoes 3 to 4 minutes, rotating halfway through cooking time.
In glass casserole, blend potatoes, cheese, flour, onion, salt, pepper and chives.
Cook, covered, 6 to 8 minutes, rotating halfway through cooking time. Rest, covered, 5 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form into 2 balls.
Roll in chopped nuts, parsley or bacon bits.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: saucy chicken-cheese sandwich
directions: In saucepan, blend chicken soup, milk and cheese.
Add the cubed, cooked chicken.
Heat until cheese melts; stir now and then.
Place cooked and drained asparagus on 4 slices of toast; top with sauce. Yields 4 servings.
Garnish with 2 thin pimento strips.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish.
Sprinkle each with salt and pepper.
On each chop, place a slice of lemon cut about 1/4-inch thick, then sprinkle a teaspoon brown sugar over each chop.
Mix together catsup and water; pour around chops until they are just covered.
Bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Serves 6.

title: tossed greek salad
directions: Combine greens and cut up vegetables. In a dressing shaker, mix olive oil, vinegar, water, salt, pepper, oregano, dill, lemon juice and crushed garlic. Toss with just enough dressing to coat (refrigerate extra dressing for future use). Garnish with Feta cheese, beets and olives.

title: cool key lime drink
directions: Put in container with tight-fitted lid. Shake until blended. Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs. Serve immediately.

title: ham pie
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in oil.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour, milk, cream of chicken soup and chopped pimiento.
Stir in ham and lemon juice.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with canned biscuits.
Spread grated cheese over biscuits.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until biscuits are brown and casserole is bubbly.

title: shrimp salad(a creole recipe)
directions: Combine rice, shrimp, salt, lemon juice, green pepper, onion, olives and cauliflower in salad bowl, toss. Combine French dressing, pepper and mayonnaise, mix well. Spoon over salad, chill thoroughly. Serve on a lettuce bed. 4 servings.

title: ginger pork
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Stir-fry the pork and garlic for 3 minutes. Combine soy sauce, sugar & ginger. Add to skillet. Reduce to medium heat. Stir fry 3-4 minutes more or until pork is no longer pink. Combine cornstarch and water and mix until smooth. Add to skillet. Bring to boil. Boil and stir for 2 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Rub chicken with salt and pepper.
Heat butter in a skillet and brown chicken on all sides.
Remove chicken to crock-pot and saute onions, garlic and parsley in the same butter for a minute or two.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and cook for 4 to 5 hours on low.

title: strawberry dessert(baker's hall of fame)
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, oleo and nuts and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: glorified grahams
directions: Line 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with graham cracker squares.
Mix butter and brown sugar.
Spoon over graham crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 12 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.
Break into squares. Makes 2 dozen.

title: hot shrimp puffs
directions: *Can also use crab or mushrooms.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook together the sugar, water, syrup and salt until mixture forms a hard ball in cold water.
Add the peanuts and stir until they are thoroughly parched.
Remove from the heat and add baking soda.
Pour onto a greased marble slab until cold.
Stretch the slightly cooled peanut brittle with buttered hands so there is more to go around for the family and friends.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Add Knox gelatine plus heated water to tomato soup.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Blend all in the blender.
Makes 3 glass bowls.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, water and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick and clear.
Add Jell-O.
Pour half into pie shell.
Arrange strawberries into Jell-O mixture.
Pour remaining mixture over strawberries. Refrigerate until congealed.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sidewalk ice cream(children's)
directions: Place ingredients in a 1 pound coffee can; put lid on small can and tape with wide masking tape so it will not leak out. Place small can inside a 3 pound coffee can.
Put ice and rock salt around the small can; place lid on top of large can and roll between two people for about 15 minutes.
You may need to add more salt and ice after about 10 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix oil and eggs.
Add eggs and mix well.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients alternating with buttermilk.
Add vinegar, vanilla, and food coloring and mix well. Bake three layers of 8 or 9-inch greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350 until cake springs back when lightly pressed in the center. Cool 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine beef with bread crumbs, salt, pepper and garlic; mix until well blended. Add celery, onions, sweet peppers, eggs, milk, water and tomato juice. Mix lightly but thoroughly. Avoid overmixing. Shape into 8 loaves weighing about 5 3/4 pounds. Place loaves in each pan. Bake 2 hours or until meat thermometer registers an internal temperature of 165°. Skim off excess fat and liquid during cooking period. Let stand 20 minutes before slicing. Cut 13 slices per loaf.

title: best rum cake ever
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good isn't it?
Now go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the rum again.
It must be just right.
Be sure the rum is of the highest quality; pour 1 level cup of rum into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat... with an electric mixer, beat 1 cup batter in large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon thugar and beat again.
Meanwhile, make sure that the rum is of the finest quality.
Try another cup.
Open second quart, if necessary.
Add 2 arge leggs, 2 cups fried druit and beat until high.
If druit gets stuck in beaters, just pry it loose with crewscriver.
Sample rum again, checking for tonscisticity.
Next sift 3 cups of pepper or salt (it really doesn't matter).
Sample rum again.
Sift 1/2 pint lemon joice.
Fold in chopped butter and your strained nuts.
Add 1 bablespoon of brown thugar or whatever color you find.
Wix well.
Grease over and turn cake pan to 350°. Now, pour the whole mess into the coven...and brake.
Check the rum again and go to bed.

title: fruit cobbler pie
directions: Melt oleo in 10 x 6-inch pan.
Mix sugar, self-rising flour and milk.
Pour mixture down center of pan.
Add filling and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown and done.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix two ingredients together.
Pour over 3 pounds of spareribs or meat balls.
Cook in oven, covered, at 350° for 2 1/2 hours or crock-pot for 4 hours.

title: low calorie baked pineapple squares
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Put in loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.
One serving equals 1 egg, 1 bread and 1 fruit.

title: marinated salad
directions: Bring the first 6 ingredients to a boil; set aside and let cool.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour mixture over. Let set in refrigerator overnight; drain.
Ready to eat.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles. Press perforations together to seal.
Place 8 pepperoni slices on each rectangle.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup of Mozzarella cheese. Starting at the shortest side, tightly roll up each rectangle. Pinch to seal.
Slice each roll into 4 equal slices.
Pinch dough together on one side of each slice to seal.
Place sealed side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook in 4-quart pan over medium heat until rice is absorbed in the liquid, approximate time 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring often. Beat together 1 cup milk and 1 large egg and add to rice mixture. Continue cooking over medium heat until it reaches a boiling point, but do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and sprinkle cinnamon over top.

title: texas pecan brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients except for Marshmallow Creme.
Put batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 28 minutes.
While hot, spread with Marshmallow Creme.
Cool.
Frost.

title: ma~maw mac's dinner rolls
directions: Knead 15 or 20 minutes. Put in greased bowl. Let rise 1 hour. Punch down and knead again another 5 or 10 minutes. Put back in greased bowl and let rise again for 30 minutes. Make rolls. Let rise in warm area out of draft for another 30 minutes. Heat oven to 350°. Put in oven for 15 minutes or until done. Brush with butter.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Melt paraffin wax and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture and put on wax paper to dry.

title: different brownie bars
directions: Mix all ingredients except confectioners sugar.
Turn into lightly greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into bars while warm.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Yields 40 bars.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat 1/2 the oil in wok.
Scramble eggs.
Remove from pan. Add rest of oil.
Fry meat and scallions.
After a few minutes, add rice and vegetables, stirring constantly.
Pour in the rest of ingredients and add eggs.
Heat and serve.

title: dried beef gravy
directions: Put oleo and dried beef in pan.
Cook a few minutes.
Mix the flour with 1/2 cup of the milk.
Pour 2 1/2 cups milk in the pan with the oleo and dried beef.
Heat until boiling or hot.
Add milk and flour.
Stir until thick, turn down low and continue to cook until done.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Slice bananas into baked pie crust until bottom is covered. Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar until creamy.
Pour mixture into crust. Top with blueberries.
Chill.
It's delicious!

title: mulled cider
directions: Mix in crock-pot.
Simmer for 6 hours.
Before serving, replace orange with fresh slices.

title: caviar pie
directions: Mix cream cheese with a little milk or mayonnaise to soften; put in serving dish.
Top with onion, minced egg and caviar. Serve with crackers.

title: little applesauce muffins
directions: In large bowl, cream softened butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, until light and fluffy.
Beat in applesauce.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Spoon into 36 greased mini-muffin cups.
bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or just until golden.
While warm, dip tops or all sides into melted butter and then into cinnamon/sugar mixture. Very good served warm.
Makes 36.

title: diabetic fruit bars
directions: Boil dates, prunes, raisins and water.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add oleo.
Mix flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add fruit mixture.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
If you care for spice taste, add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles.
Layer noodles, hamburger, cottage cheese, sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat another layer same way.
Put in long, big dish or pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: canned deer meat
directions: In each quart jar, add all ingredients.
Place lids on jars and put them in cold pack canner.
After it starts to boil, cook for 4 hours.

title: val's bean dip
directions: Cook up all of the bacon and drain, reserve 1/8 cup the drippings in a large pan.
Add to the drippings in the following order:
Garlic powder and 1/3 of the green onions, saute for about 5 minutes.
Add can of refried beans and picante sauce and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Bring to a slow bubble and add a small handful of each kind of cheese and about 1/3 of the bacon (crumbled).
Cook and stir until the cheese is melted.
Once cheese has melted, transfer to an oven-safe casserole dish.
Layer the top of the dip in the following order:
3/4 of remaining cheeses, green onions, bacon (crumbled) and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and sides are bubbling.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Peel and cut eggplant in cubes; boil in water until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and mash.
Combine eggplant, white sauce, cheese, onions, seasonings and beaten eggs.
(A cup of rice can be used to make cornbread stick together.
If using rice, use a little more liquid.) Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour or until onions are tender.

title: caitlin's healthy french toast
directions: Mix eggs, milk and cinnamon-sugar.
Saturate bread slices until mixture is absorbed.
Coat bread in oatmeal.
Pan fry in margarine.
Top with lite syrup and banana slices or strawberries.

title: cream of avocado soup(cool, simple and elegant)
directions: *Use more chicken broth, if desired, and less evaporated milk.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in baking pan; mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg with fork and sprinkle over apples.
Melt margarine and pour over topping; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix the ingredients thoroughly with a mixer for 10 minutes. When well mixed, place in greased pan (13 x 9-inch) for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

When done, remove cake from the oven and prick with large fork all over and all the way down through cake. Mix 1 cup powdered sugar with 1 cup of freshly squeezed lemons. Pour this mixture over the cake.

title: candied yams
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Peel sweet potatoes; cut lengthwise.
Put in pot and simmer until tender.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth.
Beat in the peanut butter, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill before serving.

title: graham squares
directions: Mix together crumbs, marshmallows, walnuts, cherries and milk. Put layer of coconut on bottom of pan.
Add mixture.
Cover with coconut; refrigerate.

title: green beans with mushroom sauce
directions: Drain green beans and place in casserole.
Mix mushroom soup with 1/2 can water.
Stir until smooth, then pour over green beans.
Sprinkle with onion rings and bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes or until bubbling.
Cover casserole until ready to serve.

title: clam dip
directions: Beat eggs and add oil and cheese.
Mix in clams (do not drain).
Stir in bread crumbs until oatmeal mixture.
Chill.
Add extra spices if desired to taste (parsley, oregano, garlic, salt and pepper).
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together in order given.
Place in a 2-quart oblong casserole, buttered.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and water together and cook until clear. Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Pour over whole strawberries in graham cracker crust or baked pastry pie shell. Top with whipped topping or whipped cream.
Garnish with strawberries.
Chill.

title: greek pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta al dente; rinse, drain and cool.
Mix in salad dressing and olives.
Chill overnight.
Just before serving, crumble Feta cheese over top.

title: 4 layer chocolate pie
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, chopped nuts and margarine; pat in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: green beans with oil
directions: Clean beans and cut into small pieces; place pan on stove. Heat pan; then place oil in it.
Cut the garlic and onion, then place in pan.
After onion and garlic get brown, add the green beans, salt and allspice into pan, then cover it.
Peel the tomatoes, then cut into small pieces and add to the green beans. Stir and keep in stove 30 to 40 minutes.

title: iowa maid rites
directions: Cook the beef, salt and pepper until done; drain, then add the Coke.
Steam well.
Brown onions on side.
Serve on bun with catsup, mustard, pickle and fried onions.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Place cut up chicken on bottom of casserole dish or baking pan.
Mix soup and broth in saucepan; heat and pour over chicken. Mix remaining ingredients together; pour over soup and broth mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes, or until brown and bubbly.

title: sweet skillet meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, 1/4 cup water, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Set aside.
In a large skillet, bring remaining water to a boil, add the bouillon cubes, brown sugar, raisins, lemon juice and gingersnaps.
Stir until thoroughly combined.
Add meatballs to skillet.
Simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes, until meat is no longer pink.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over noodles.
Yields 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish.
Break up crackers and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade peanut brittle
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar, butter and salt.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Then add raw peanuts.
Stir constantly until peanuts turn light brown.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in the soda and spread thinly on greased platter.

title: chocolate sauce for ice cream
directions: Boil the mixture for about 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve hot in a pitcher, pouring over your favorite ice cream.
Upon contact with ice cream it becomes hard and chewy.

title: playdough(not edible)
directions: Mix well in a large cooking pot.
Stir continuously over medium heat until the mixture is doughlike and not too sticky to the touch.
Let cool; enjoy!

title: calico beans
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well with browned meat and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix apricot jello, sugar and boiling water together.
Cream the cream cheese.
Add pineapple, apricot baby food and chopped nuts.
Mix with jello mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip; mix well. Refrigerate until firm.

title: poppy seed dressing for fruit or greens
directions: To make onion juice, grate medium onion on fine side of grater or chop in processor; strain over bowl and reserve juice.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water 20 minutes. Drain. Fry bacon. Set aside. Mix into the bacon drippings the flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper. Cook until just beginning to bubble. Add water and vinegar. Heat to boiling (1 minute). Crumble in bacon and add potatoes. Stir and serve.

title: chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until well done.
Take out of water and let cool. Make biscuit mix according to box.
Roll out biscuits and cut into small portions. Drop into pot of hot broth.
Take meat from bone and put into pot.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until dumplings are well done.
Serve.

title: "t" wings or "t & a" wings
directions: Rinse chicken wings in cold water.
Preheat oven to 350°. Fold chicken wings and place one layer thick in large Corning Ware.
Cover with teriyaki sauce for "T" Wings.
Add Amaretto to teriyaki sauce;
mix and cover chicken with mixture for "T & A" Wings.
Cover and cook for 90 minutes until done.
Turn wings every 20 minutes.
Drain, cool and serve.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Soak black-eyed peas overnight.
(Instead you may bring to boil and let stand for 1 hour.)
Combine peas, water, bouillon, onion, garlic, thyme, vegetable oil and salt in Dutch oven or large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer gently for 1 hour or until tender.
Add additional water if peas become too thick.

title: grandpa vinnie's egg drops for soup
directions: Have broth from chicken boiling.
Beat 1 egg.
Add salt.
Add water and stir to make a smooth paste.
Add flour and mix.
Take a real thin sliver off of spoon and drop into boiling broth.
It will come to top.
Cook just a little longer and serve.
If I don't have enough mix and if there is a lot of broth, I mix up another batch.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Beat egg; add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in vinegar, then milk.
Cook over low heat and stir until slightly thickened; cool.
Stir in sour cream.
Mix with freshly grated cabbage when ready to serve.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Use large microwave container, one that pours is good. Combine sugar and syrup in bowl; cook on High 4 minutes.
Add peanuts; stir.
Cook on High 4 minutes.
Add margarine, salt and vanilla; stir and cook on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from microwave; add baking soda.
Fold into hot mixture (it will puff up).
Pour onto greased cookie sheet; do not spread with spoon, it takes the air out of the candy.

title: succotash
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer over low heat until beans are soft and liquid is nearly gone for fresh beans and canned beans. Simmer until liquid reaches the consistency of thin gravy.
Add seasonings to taste.
Add butter, if desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and form a loaf and cover with the sauce.

title: homemade brownies
directions: Melt
butter
and
cocoa,
then add sugar, eggs, flour, vanilla and the
chopped nuts.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low-fat chicken
directions: Take chicken breasts, skin and get all fat off that you can. Place in bowl; pour buttermilk over.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to cook, take out of milk; salt and pepper to taste.
Then crush cornflakes and batter.
Place in an uncovered pan and bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and layer the graham crackers on the bottom of the pan. (Keep the crackers whole). Mix together the pudding and milk and let set in the refrigerator for about 5 minutes. Mix the Cool Whip with the pudding and spread over the graham crackers. Layer another layer of graham crackers and another layer of pudding mixture. Put the last layer of graham crackers on the top of pudding mixture. Spread the icing over the graham crackers. Refrigerate. This is better made a day ahead of time.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Brown chicken lightly in butter; add celery, onion, salt, chicken broth and pepper.
Cook, covered, about 15 minutes or until celery and onion are tender.
Add Chinese vegetables and mushrooms.
Heat to a boiling point and add cornstarch mixed with soy sauce.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Serve with chop suey noodles.

title: two cheese broccoli
directions: Cook the broccoli and drain.
Add all ingredients and place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 325° or until golden brownish and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Reserve 1/2 to 3/4 cup nuts.
Combine all other ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.
Shape into ball or log.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Refrigerate until serving time. Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: salsa dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese to room temperature (45 seconds in the microwave and then stir until soft). Add the sour cream. In another bowl, combine the chili and salsa. Use a 2-quart or larger glass bowl and put a layer of half the white sauce, a layer of half the red sauce and 1 cup of grated cheese. Repeat the layers. Microwave 8 to 10 minutes until hot and bubbly. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine lemonade, Cool Whip, condensed milk and food coloring. Pour into crusts. You may put some Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: creole vegetable casserole
directions: Combine tomatoes, drained corn, green pepper, celery, onion, salt, pepper and rice.
Mix well and pour into 1-quart casserole. Crush stuffing into coarse crumbs and mix with melted butter. Sprinkle over vegetables and rice mixture.
Bake uncovered at 425° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: torchette, italian cookies
directions: Put the first four ingredients in a bowl and mix well with a fork (like free dough).
Add flour to make a soft dough.
Let rise for at least 1/2 hour.
Work in with a small piece of dough at a time, roll out like a pencil.
The thinner, the better (use about 5-inch each).
Dip into granulated sugar.
Form into heart shape on
a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Put sugar side up. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Put under broiler to glaze top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix sugar and Jell-O; pour in water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add pineapple, cranberries, marshmallows and nuts.
Pour in a dish; let sit in refrigerator until firm or overnight.

title: baking clay
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Knead for 10 minutes until mixture is slightly pliable.
Roll out 1/3 inch thick.
Use any cookie cutters and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Moisten bread crumbs in milk.
Combine with beef, salt and pepper.
Roll into balls.
Place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over balls.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine soup and broth; mix well.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat, add chives, mushrooms and cheese; stir until cheese has melted.
Spoon half the rice into a 3-quart buttered casserole, top with half the chicken and then half the sauce.
Repeat with remaining rice, chicken and sauce.
Sprinkle pimento over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: macaroni ring salad
directions: Cook macaroni rings, drain and cool.
Mix Mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Mix with macaroni rings and vegetables.

title: potato au gratin
directions: Melt butter; add onion, pepper and pimentos.
Saute until tender.
Mix flour, salt and milk.
Add the milk mixture, cheese and soup.
Pour over diced potatoes.
Place grated cheese on top. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or more.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix.
Spread evenly in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Chill before serving.
Serve with chips.

title: roast marinade
directions: Pat roast all over with black pepper and poppy seed.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over roast.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 2 days.
Cook (covered) for 3 to 4 hours at 300° or until done (with marinade).
Use marinade for sauce when serving.

title: tennessee chicken kiev
directions: Cook and chop chicken. Layer in bottom of 9 x 13 inch pan. Mix milk and soup and pour over chicken. Put margarine, packet of seasoning mix from Stove Top Dressing and chicken broth in pan. Bring to a boil. Add stuffing crumbs, stir and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: quick ambrosia
directions: About 10 minutes before serving, slice banana.
Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks in medium bowl.
Mix banana, oranges and pineapple with fruit cocktail with its juice.
Spoon into serving dishes; sprinkle with coconut.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix together and press in pan.

title: creamy onion dip
directions: Beat or blend sour cream with mix until thoroughly blended. Chill.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all these ingredients in a boiler and cook for 10 or 15 minutes on low heat.
Will make over a quart of barbecue sauce.

title: apple pizza pie
directions: Combine creamer, sugars, flour, salt and spices in bowl.
Mix well.
Sprinkle 1/2 mixture over pastry.
Cut butter into remaining mixture until crumbly.
Set aside.
Arrange apples in rings, overlapping.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Top with crumbly mixture.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: italian sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, cover bottom of pan with olive oil.
Saute onion, sweet basil and parsley, cooking at medium heat.
Add the tomato puree and 1/2 can of water for each can.
Stir often so sauce won't stick to bottom of pan.
Cook 4 to 6 hours.

title: spring pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water (or steam, if fresh); drain.
Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon with sour cream.
Mix dressing, mustard and garlic together; pour over salad mixture.
Toss gently. Chill.

title: jan hagel cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Add flour and cinnamon. Pat flat on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with egg white and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° until brown (about 20 minutes). Cut while warm.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine beans and taco mix.
Spread on plate.
Smooth sour cream on top.
Sprinkle remaining chopped ingredients over top. Refrigerate until served.
Serve with taco chips.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook on High for 8 minutes. (Stir after 4 minutes.)
Add butter and vanilla; stir and microwave 2 more minutes.
Add baking soda and quickly stir until light and foamy.
Immediately pour onto lightly buttered baking sheet; spread thin.
Cool, then break into pieces.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour (optional), sugar and salt together in saucepan. Combine oleo, water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour mix.
In another bowl, mix eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add flour mix and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 10 1/2 x 12 1/2-inch jelly roll pan or 9 x 13-inch or 11 x 7-inch or 17 1/2 x 11 1/4-inch.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot bran muffins
directions: Mix bran, eggs and vegetable oil and let set for 5 minutes. Then add brown sugar, molasses, grated carrots and raisins.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Grease muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 24 large muffins.

title: hot spiced fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups syrup.
Put drained fruit in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Core and dice apples and mix with lemon juice and then toss with rest of fruit.
Stir together syrup, brown sugar and spices and pour over fruit.
Dot with butter. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add cut bananas and grapes.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion and saute until onion is tender.
In a large soup pot, add meat mixture and remaining ingredients.
Cook until carrots and potatoes are tender.
Serve with hot bread.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
(Tastes like pecan pie.)

title: high protein bread
directions: Combine yeast, water and honey.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Mix and Gradually add dry ingredients and oil.
Blend and turn out on floured board, adding additional flour as needed.
Knead thoroughly until dough is smooth and elastic.
Place in a well-oiled bowl. Let rise until doubled.
Punch dough down; fold over the edges and turn dough upside down.
Let it rise another 20 minutes.
Turn out on board.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place in oiled pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: six cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: mother's favorite chicken dumplings
directions: Cook until chicken is tender, remove and put dumplings in the liquid and cook until done.

title: swiss veggies
directions: Combine the vegetables, soup, 1/2 the cheese, sour cream and 1/2 the onions.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, another 5 minutes.

title: chicken with almonds
directions: Brown chicken with garlic in butter.
Add almonds and brown. Stir in soup and cream.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate morsels, milk and butter. Remove from heat.
Combine nuts and marshmallows with chocolate mixture and drop on waxed paper.
Makes 40 pieces.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients together, stirring occasionally.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly (shouldn't boil over 5 minutes).
Add pecans.
Whip with spoon for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Drop on wax paper.
Should start to harden within 5 to 7 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Place chocolate pieces in food processor and chop finely, turning machine on and off, scraping chocolate down from sides of the bowl.
Add hot coffee and sugar and process until blended. Add egg yolks and rum gradually; continue processing until mixture is well blended.
Pour mixture into a bowl and fold in egg whites. Chill thoroughly before serving.
Serves 8.

title: fireworks
directions: Mix boiled beans (drained) in beer and let sit for 1 to 2 hours.
Slice green pepper and bacon in short, fine slices.
Add barbecue sauce to beans/beer and bring to a rapid boil over medium heat.
Transfer to an ovenproof pan.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: old time pound cake
directions: Sift flour, then measure. Then sift 3 more times. Cream butter and sugar. Add flavors.
Add 2 eggs and 1 cup flour at a time until all is mixed. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: apple tea
directions: Place spices in 8 cups water.
Bring to boil and simmer with tea bags for a few minutes (covered).
Add sugar, lemon and apple juice.
Remove tea bags, turn off heat and allow spices to steep for a few minutes.
When ready to serve, strain tea to remove spices.
Serve hot or iced.
Can refrigerate for 2 or 3 days. Adjust spices to taste.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Combine and pour over beef mixture.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Serve over hamburger buns.

title: pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Beat in next 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven 55 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: baked beans with hamburger
directions: Brown beef in fat, use heavy skillet.
Add onion.
Simmer until onion is barely tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole, cover.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: beefy rice creole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add onion and garlic.
Drain tomatoes into 1-quart measure.
Chop tomatoes and add to tomato liquid.
Add enough water to make 2 1/4 cups liquid.
Combine tomato mixture, rice, A.1. steak sauce, green pepper, salt and celery in skillet.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: squash relish
directions: Sprinkle salt over ground vegetables.
Mix last 5 ingredients.
Let come to a boil.
Add vegetable mixture.
Let come to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Put into hot sterile jars.
Seal.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: jackson's pasta
directions: While pasta is cooking, get all other ingredients ready. Chicken should be hot when pasta is done. Drain pasta. Return to pot. Add all cut up ingredients and then add Dijon dressing until moist. Stir until hot.

title: key lime pie(from key west)
directions: Combine milk and egg yolks at slow speed.
Slowly add juice, mixing until well blended.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate overnight.
Top with whipped cream or meringue.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix the sugar, salt, margarine and milk; boil on medium-low heat for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Combine German chocolate, chocolate chips and marshmallow cream with hot ingredients; mix with electric mixer.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.
When cool, store in tin in cool place.

title: play dough
directions: Put all ingredients in a saucepan.
Let cook, stirring constantly until a ball forms.
Take off heat.
Knead until smooth.
Store in an airtight container.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, egg, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl until smooth.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt and add to shortening mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll cookie dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut out with cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: jello pie(sugar-free)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add cold water.
Chill until very thick.
Meanwhile, prepare instant pudding with milk as directed on package.
Let stand until set, about 5 minutes.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine egg and milk; add to flour and mix all at once.
Stir until dough follows fork around bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured surface; knead gently with heal of hand, about 20 strokes.
Roll dough to 3/4-inch thickness and cut with floured cutter.
Place on ungreased pan 3/4-inches apart for crusty biscuits, close together for soft sided.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: barbecue string beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion; add rest of ingredients and simmer for 2 minutes.
Put beans in casserole and pour bacon mixture over. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Add zucchini and pineapple.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: green peas and mushrooms
directions: Pour peas and juice into baking dish.
Mix in a can of mushroom soup and garlic powder.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 400° in oven until bubbly and heated through.

title: honey-glazed carrots
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine carrots, lemon peel strip, honey and salt.
Add enough cold water to cover carrots.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, boiling until the liquid nearly evaporates, about 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium, stir carrot mixture until coated with glaze.
Remove pan from heat.
Add lemon juice, tarragon (optional), nutmeg and pepper to pan; mix well.
Place carrot mixture in serving dish, garnish with grated lemon peel and serve immediately.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli. Drain and chop. Mix soups with broccoli. Heat, then add sour cream and serve.

title: whitney pot roast
directions: Place steaks in cold water overnight.
The next day, pat dry and season with salt, pepper and paprika.
In a skillet, quickly brown steaks with butter or oil.
Remove meat from skillet and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic until transparent and add remaining ingredients.
Place meat in heavy roast pan and pour onion mixture over it.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove spice bag and bay leaves.
Thicken liquid with flour and water.
Serve.

title: corn flake potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes.
Put into a cake pan. Cover with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
In a baking pan, layer 1/2 broccoli, crackers, margarine and cheese.
Repeat with another layer.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven until the cheese is melted.
Enjoy.

title: no weep meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, 2 tablespoons sugar and water in saucepan. Cook gently until thickened; cool.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Add 6 tablespoons of sugar gradually, beating constantly. Add vanilla and mix well.
Continue beating while adding cooled mixture.
Beat until very stiff.
Pile on pie and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown beef; drain and cool.
Mix with beans, tomatoes, cheese, onion and lettuce.
Make dressing from mayonnaise, pickle relish and catsup.
Pour over all chips and arrange avocado on top.

title: mexican cajun quickie
directions: Brown the ground meat.
Add the beans and chili powder to taste.
When cooked and about ready to serve, crunch in the Doritos.
Serve over lettuce and tomato.
Top with sour cream and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine zwiback, 1 cup sugar, melted butter and cinnamon. Press mixture in bottom and on sides of greased 9-inch spring-form pan, reserving 3/4 cup for topping.
Beat eggs with sugar until fluffy.
Add salt and lemon juice and rind.
Stir in cream, cream cheese and flour.
Press until mixture is well blended.
Pour over crust and sprinkle with reserved topping and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: applesauce drop cookies
directions: Mix raisins and applesauce; set aside.
Combine sugar, shortening and egg.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in applesauce and raisins.
Combine next 6 ingredients; mix well.
Stir in nuts. Drop soft dough by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: top of the stove rice pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook slowly until rice is tender.
Beat egg or egg whites in water with whisk.
Add vanilla to egg and water mixture.
Add mixture to rice.
If using whole egg, add some of the hot rice mixture to egg and water so as not to have the egg separate when added to rice.
Cook for 2 more minutes.
Pour into bowl and sprinkle with cinnamon.
This will thicken more when refrigerated.

title: nancy's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes after dicing up, also boil eggs.
Fry your bacon.
Mash all above ingredients together and you have Nancy's Potato Salad.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Layer all of the smoked sausage on bottom of dish.
Add all the sliced potatoes.
Add green pepper and onion, if desired.
Set aside.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in greased muffin tins. Sprinkle tops with poppy seed.
Bake at 425° until browned.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and make into small meatballs.
Place in casserole dish.

title: muriel's golden recipe for toll house cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Dissolve 1 teaspoon baking soda with 1/4 cup hot water.
Mix alternately with baking powder, flour, salt and vanilla and all the ingredients (mixed) except nuts and chocolate chips.
Lastly, add the nuts (optional) and the chocolate chips.
Chill overnight, if possible.
Roll in greased palm of hand and drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 50 cookies.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs and flour.
Mix well.
Add pineapple, pecans, cinnamon and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour in tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Glaze.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a bowl; mix well. Pour into graham cracker crust. Top with your favorite topping. Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix butter and stuffing; place half in bottom of pan.
Mix other ingredients; pour over stuffing mixture.
Put other half of stuffing mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: company casserole no. 2000
directions: Brown the meats until crumbly (remove casing from Italian sausage).
Add the salt, pepper and spaghetti sauce.
Mix tomato sauce and tomato paste and combine thoroughly.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook the macaroni according to the directions on the package; drain and combine with cooked sauce.
Spread 1/2 the meat mixture over the bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 drained spinach.
Dot evenly with 1/2 the sour cream mixed with grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Spread to make an even layer.
Sprinkle with 1/2 Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with Parmesan cheese.

title: pepperoni pizza spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend together cream cheese, sour cream, garlic powder, oregano and red pepper in small bowl.
Spread cream cheese mixture in a pie plate.
Spread pizza sauce over cream cheese layer.
Top with green onion, green pepper, Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes.
Serve warm on Melba toast or pieces of fresh bread.

title: quick and hearty casserole
directions: Mix meat with beaten eggs, Worcestershire sauce, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Brown hamburg lightly in skillet with melted butter.
Add Veg-All and juice along with tomato paste to meat. Heat, stirring.

title: glazed chicken breast
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Place chicken, skin side down, in baking dish.
Pour half the sauce over them.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn pieces and spread with the rest of the sauce.
Bake 1/2 hour more or until tender.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Grease sheet pans.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing until well blended.
Spread batter in pans 1/2-inch deep.
Bake
35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost with fudge frosting.

title: strawberry lemonade
directions: Squeeze lemons; strain seeds and pulp for 1/2 cup juice. Cover and refrigerate.
Place 4 cups water, sugar, salt and berries into a pan. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Stir to crush berries and dissolve sugar (about 2 minutes). Cool and refrigerate.

title: chocolate chess pie 2
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Mix eggs, butter, milk and vanilla.
Add nuts and blend all together.
Put in two unbaked pie shells.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: edna's special cake
directions: Put layers of each in order given in oblong cake pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chili for nesco roaster
directions: Brown and fry beef.
Cook celery and onions.
Mix all ingredients in Nesco roaster.
You can also add macaroni elbow shells.
Simmer 2 or 3 hours.
Serves 40 to 50.

title: leftover chicken & potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In oven baking dish arrange layers of potatoes, chicken and onions.
Mix together soup and milk in small bowl.
Pour over top of layers.
Cover.
Bake for 40 minutes or till potatoes are fork tender.
Yield:
1 to 2 servings.

title: broccoli and cheese bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Stir well. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: marshmallow sauce
directions: Cut marshmallows and melt in top of double boiler.
Stir sugar into boiling water, then add to marshmallows; stir well.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Ready to serve.

title: beer fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in a pan.
In a bowl, mix sugar and salt.
Mix chocolate mixture with sugar.
Add beer, milk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Pour into a lightly buttered pan.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Place zucchini, onions and salt in a large bowl.
Mix well and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Blend butter and seasonings.
Pour over rest of ingredients mixed in pan.
Stir and salt lightly to taste. Bake 1 hour, stirring carefully every 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Melt the oleo.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and the pretzels.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool thoroughly. Mix the jello with the boiling water.
Add strawberries until partially set.
Mix the cream cheese with the Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar.
Spread over the cooled pretzel crust.
Top with jello mixture.
Chill several hours.

title: roasted mustard potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a roasting pan 3 times to coat with vegetable oil.
Place remaining ingredients in a bowl. Blend.
Add potatoes and toss.
Pour potatoes into roasting pan. Bake 45 minutes to an hour, until potatoes are tender.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Roll and place on baking sheet.

title: grandma lester's cucumbers with sour cream and pecan dressing
directions: Mix sour cream, chopped pecans, grated onion, lemon juice and salt.
Peel 2 cucumbers and slice thin.
Chill.
Add dressing and toss lightly.
Serve on greens.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Add remaining ingredients. Heat in oven until bubbly hot.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except French fried onions. Let stand overnight or bake right away. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Last 10 minutes, top with French fried onions.

title: molasses banana bread
directions: *Optional:
Substitute 1/2 cup milk for milk powder and water.

title: do it yourself soda pop
directions: Reconstitute frozen juice with club soda instead of water.

title: quick praline bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange graham crackers in single layer in ungreased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Heat brown sugar and butter to boiling.
Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Heat oil in large casserole or Dutch oven.
Add onions; saute over medium heat until softened or about 5 minutes.
Add cabbage and salt.
Cover and cook over low heat, stirring often, until cabbage is wilted or about 5 minutes.
Add rice, cumin, garlic and turmeric; saute about 2 minutes.
Stir in broth, more salt, if needed, and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 (main dish) or 6 to 8 (side dish).

title: delicious zucchini
directions: Saute zucchini, mushrooms and onions in oil 10 minutes until tender but not mushy.
Remove from heat.
Toss lightly with 1/3 cup grated cheese.
Add rest of ingredients and toss.
Turn into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Sift again with soda and salt. Cream shortening.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add sour milk and flour.
Add nuts, cherries, dates and candied fruit.
Chill dough for several hours.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 2-inches apart, on lightly greased baking sheet.
Top each cookie with half a candied cherry.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix real well and finish filling freezer up with milk.
Add fruit if you want to peaches, strawberries, bananas, etc.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Blend in potato by mashing it slightly against the side of pan with a fork.

title: chicken kabobs
directions: Skin boned chicken breasts.
Cut in 1 inch pieces; put aside. Combine and mix well: oil, soy sauce, sesame seed, lemon juice, ginger, wine, corn syrup and garlic powder.
Mix with chicken and marinate 2 hours.
Cut the pineapple, onions, green pepper and zucchini in 1 inch squares.
Alternate on skewers and grill 6 inches from medium hot coals, turning and basting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: It takes just 10 minutes to make these hot canapes that melt in your mouth.
Keep a supply in your freezer.
Excellent with soup or a salad for a luncheon.

title: alsie's upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Lightly grease oblong pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut in pan. Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix well the powdered sugar, cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Spoon mixture over uncooked cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch in pan.
Cook until very thick.
Add Jell-O to hot mixture and stir well.
Cool completely. Add strawberries to mixture.
Stir.
Pour into baked pie crust. Chill.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: real good pie crust
directions: Cut together with pastry blender the shortening with the flour, with the salt added.
Into a 1-cup measure, break the whole egg and beat.
Add the vinegar, then mix.
Finish filling cup with ice water.
Pour this mixture over the flour-shortening mixture. Stir together; form into large ball.

title: mushrooms with cucumbers
directions: In skillet, cook mushrooms, cucumbers and onion in butter for 5 to 6 minutes or just until tender, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
In a bowl, stir flour into the sour cream. Gradually stir chicken broth and parsley into sour cream mixture. Pour over vegetables.
Heat through over low heat, stirring constantly.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: dolmathes(stuffed grape leaves with meat)
directions: Blend meat, rice, onion, parsley, mint, egg, tomato sauce, broth, butter, salt and pepper together.
Mix well.
Fresh grape leaves should be put in hot water for about 5 minutes to make them pliable.
Canned leaves should be rinsed in water.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil potatoes and chicken in separate pans, then let stand to cool.
Cut potatoes and chicken in pieces and place in mixing bowl.
Add gravy and mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with stuffing and melted butter.
Place in oven at 375° and bake for 1 half hour.

title: oriental cabbage salad]
directions: Crush (or break apart) noodles slightly; place in colander. Pour boiling water over noodles to soften.
Drain well.
In a large mixing bowl, combine noodles, cabbage, onions and sesame seed.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, coarsely chop apples (large bite size). Stir together remaining ingredients, except butter. Add butter to dry ingredients and use potato masher to mix well. Mixture will be coarse. Spoon over apples and microwave for 12 to 15 minutes until apples are tender or bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: homestyle noodles with cheese
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions.
In medium saucepan, combine chicken broth, onion flakes, celery flakes, salt, garlic, parsley flakes, Molly McButter and black pepper; simmer and cook over low heat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add cheese to broth and stir and simmer until cheese is melted.
Pour over prepared and drained noodles and serve.
Entire recipe makes 6 servings.

title: barbecued chicken livers
directions: Rinse liver and drain on absorbent paper.
Mix all ingredients to make sauce and let the liver stand in sauce for 30 minutes. Spoon livers with sauce into greased shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, turning livers once.
Serve hot, inserting a pick into each liver or serve as an entree with hot rice and chopped green onions sprinkled on livers.

title: angel rolls
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in Crisco.

title: jello custard
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients as boiled custard.
Add Jell-O.
Stir until Jell-O is completely dissolved.
Let cool and add pineapple and marshmallows.
When mixture starts to jell, gently fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites and cream, whipped.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo, cocoa and salt.
Mix in eggs and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour, soda and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add boiling water all at once.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Do not be afraid to beat this cake.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and strawberries.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt, soda and cinnamon; sift together.
Add these dry ingredients to egg mixture; mix well. Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: mickey's mighty dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add all ingredients to large, heavier pot and simmer until tastes blend together and cheese is melted, about 1/2 to 1 hour.
Serve with taco chips.
Enjoy.

title: carrot salad
directions: Pour over carrot mixture and marinate.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs, flour and sugar; add rest of ingredients.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie pans.
Bake at 350°
until done.
It makes its own crust.

title: pig eating cake
directions: Mix the ingredients together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt ruth's chocolate pie
directions: Beat yolks and add dry ingredients.
Slowly add milk and mix until smooth.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into pie shell (baked).

title: banana-pineapple pie
directions: Slice bananas in the bottom of pie crust.
Mix together cream cheese, milk and pudding mix until well blended.
Spoon evenly over bananas.
Spoon drained pineapple over the pudding mixture. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
(Banana slices may be added on top, if desired.)

title: homemade irish creme liquor
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth. Serve over ice, if desired.
Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator up to one month.
Stir before serving.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Beat shortening in a large bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg and molasses; mix thoroughly.
Combine flour, soda, salt, ginger and cinnamon. Add mixture 1/4 at a time to creamed mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix and congeal until firm.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Heat Ragu sauce with garlic powder in microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Mix Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese and egg together. Pour out 1 1/2 cups Ragu for top.
Put half of sauce in a baking dish; then layer of uncooked noodles, then mixture of Ricotta cheese and then Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
Then put the 1 1/2 cups of sauce on top.
Cover with Stretch-tite to keep in moisture. Microwave on High for 5 minutes; then 20 minutes on Medium-high.

title: pecan brownies
directions: While butter melts, mix sugar, pecans, flour and cocoa in large bowl.
Add melted butter, vanilla and eggs to dry ingredients.
Mix well with spoon.
Pour into pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: ginger pork - butaniku no shogayaki
directions: Combine first four ingredients and marinate pork for 15 minutes.
Trim the sprouts.
Slice the carrot into julienne strips about 1 1/2-inches long.
Quarter and seed the peppers.
Heat the vegetable oil.
Drain the pork, reserving marinade, and saute over high heat for about 1 minute.
When the meat is nearly cooked through, add the marinade and gently shake the pan to thoroughly coat the pieces.
Remove the pork and set aside.
Add vegetables and saute briefly.
Remove from the heat when the vegetables are cooked, but still crisp.
Arrange the pork and vegetables on individual serving dishes.
Serves 4.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add flour, soda, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Stir in Rice Krispies and oats.
Drop small spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: In a large bowl, sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Bring to a boil the butter, oil and Coke, then pour over the sifted ingredients.
Add the buttermilk or sour milk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Beat batter until smooth, then fold in marshmallows. Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread marshmallows around with spatula.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Place meat in large Dutch oven or heavy baking pan (with lid). Corning Ware works well.
Combine beer, sugar and chili sauce and pour over meat.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 to 4 hours, until meat is tender.
Strain seeds out of liquid.
Cool and refrigerate overnight.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, oranges and apples.
Dissolve Jell-O in 3 cups hot water and add sugar.
Stir in cranberries, oranges and apples that have been ground together and chopped nuts.
Pour into a large pan.
Let set until firm and jelled good.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Mix all ingredients and put in a casserole dish.
Add cheese on top and bake at 350° until bubbly and hot through.

title: super easy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to simmering stage and simmer, about 15 minutes to blend flavors and thicken slightly.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Layer cooked chicken in casserole dish.
Salt and pepper. Combine remaining ingredients.
Add a little chicken broth if it seems too thick.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble corn flakes over top and drizzle 1 tablespoon butter on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: scotch shortbread cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, a little at a time, and mix well. Roll into 2 rolls, thick enough to shape cookie. Leave in refrigerator overnight. Cut into 1/4-inch slices when dough is warm enough to slice.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets. Bake in 350° oven until slightly brown. Very good.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add flour mixture and milk.
Mix until well blended.
Add vanilla. Bake on 350° until toothpick inserted comes out clean, approximately 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine ingredients in two 8-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mrs. mckay's coffee cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and mix well.
Stir in eggs; add alternately the milk and flour which has been sifted with baking powder and salt.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Slowly add water and mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients.
Add eggs and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: In a large container, stir together all ingredients. Carefully pour into punch bowl.
Lay orange slices on top of punch in bowl.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello, water and marshmallows well until marshmallows melt.
Add cranberry and orange relish, crushed pineapple (drained), nuts and Cool Whip.
This can be put into a mold or bowl.
Chill until set.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Blend the soups, tomatoes and chicken broth.
Butter casserole dish and begin layering with chips, turkey, onion, sauce and cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vidalias and rice
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter in 3-quart casserole until foamy. Add onions.
Stir until well coated.
Add rice and salt.
Cook in a 300° oven about 1 hour, stirring 2 to 3 times.
Just before serving, add milk, cheese and parsley.
Stir until cheese is melted and well mixed.

title: gobs
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Spread with filling.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat the potatoes and drain off the juice. Mix all ingredients with the heated potatoes and beat with a mixer.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon on top and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: lassi-yogurt drink
directions: Mix yogurt and water together.
Add ice cubes and serve chilled.
For saltish drink, add salt.
For sweetish drink, add sugar to taste.

title: nut bark
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt candy coating, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts.
Spread into thin layer on 2 aluminum foil-lined baking sheets.
Chill 30 minutes or until firm.
Break
into chunks.
Store covered at room temperature or in refrigerator.

title: cuban creole garlic sauce
directions: In a small dish, crush the garlic; add the oregano, salt, lime juice, oil and onion.
Allow to sit together as mixed for a few minutes.
Serve as a gravy with chicken or pork.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl with mixer until well blended.

Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Stir in 1 2/3 cups mini chocolate chips; pour into crust. Bake 10 minutes. Without opening oven door, reduce temperature to 250°. Continue baking 30 minutes or just until set. Remove from oven to wire rack. Cool completely. Cover; refrigerate until thoroughly chilled. Place remaining 1/3 cup chips and whipping cream in small microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High for 20 to 30 seconds or just until chips are melted and mixture is smooth when stirred. Cool slightly; spread over top of cheesecake. Refrigerate 15 minutes or until topping is set. Cover; refrigerate leftover cheesecake.

title: dairy state fudge
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy; set aside.
In top of double boiler, melt butter and add almond bark. Heat and stir until melted.
Add cream cheese and beat until smooth and glossy.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 64 pieces.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients for a few seconds and pour into a greased 10-inch pie plate.
(There is no pie crust.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When pie is cool, it can be cut and served just like a pie.
It bakes its own crust.

title: canned fruit salad
directions: Cook pears covered with water and juice from cherries and pineapple. Add sugar and cook tender but not soft. Add pineapple when pears are half done. Add cherries when almost done. Just long enough to heat through. Be sure water covers fruit and put in hot jar. Seal. Makes about 4 quarts.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in ice cream freezer and freeze according to your ice cream makers instructions.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave.
Dip pretzels, a few at a time, into melted almond bark.
Drop onto waxed paper.

title: baked beans
directions: Add ground beef and onion to the seasoned pork and beans, then mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and then bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Have butter soft.
Add sugar and cream together well.
Stir in buttermilk.
Add vanilla, nutmeg and eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 or 50 minutes at 350°.
Place on wire rack to cool before serving.

title: mexican cheese
directions: Lightly grease 2 qt casserole dish and mix cheese and green chilies in it.
In a blender, mix eggs, flour and evaporated milk. Pour over cheese.
Bake uncovered for 1 hr at 325 F oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and bananas; mix well. Add sour milk and blend.
Add remaining ingredients; blend.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: texas-size almond cookies
directions: In a large bowl, blend sugars, butter and oil until well blended. Add almond extract and eggs; mix well. Gradually blend in all flours, baking soda and cream of tartar at low speed of electric mixer. By hand, stir in almonds and butter brickle. Chill if desired. Shape by large tablespoons into balls. Roll in sugar and place 5 inches apart on ungreased sheet. With fork dipped in sugar, flatten with crisscross pattern. Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes or until light golden brown around edges.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Brown the pork chops in a skillet.
Mix in a large casserole dish the rice, water and onion soup.
Drop in chops and cover. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rice on bottom of shallow casserole or baking dish (greased).
Pour soup and water on top. You may season with your favorite seasonings if you wish (I usually use pepper and a little salt).
Cover with lid or aluminum foil tightly.
Bake 1 hour.

title: meat-tater pie
directions: Mix crust according to package directions.
Put one crust into pie tin.
Mix all ingredients, except potatoes.
Put mixture in pie tin.
Top with potatoes.
Place second crust on top.
Make slits in top crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with warm catsup, if desired.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ice cream and peanut butter together on low speed for 1 minute. Pour into crust. Freeze until firm, about 3 hours. Warm the ice cream topping slightly and spoon over the pie. Return to the freezer. Serve with Cool Whip on each slice. Return any leftovers to the freezer.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in small bowl.
In a large bowl mix all remaining ingredients, except pecans.
Mix the 2 bowls of ingredients together, adding pecans last.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 - 12 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli deluxe
directions: Cook broccoli slightly and drain.
Saute diced celery and onion in small amount of margarine.
Dice pimento.
Place drained broccoli in bottom of buttered casserole.
Add celery, onion and the pimento.
Mix mushroom soup with sour cream.
Spoon on top of casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crab delight
directions: Marinate crab in sherry.
Cook noodles al dente and drain. In double boiler or microwave, cook cheese, half and half and butter together until smooth.
Mix crab into sauce; stir into noodles (add pimento).
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole. Top with almonds and dot with butter.
Cover and bake 20 minutes at 325° just until bubbly.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Can also bake in a casserole to serve as a side dish.
May bake, freeze and reheat. Also, cut small and use as hors d'oeuvre.

title: gogurt cookies
directions: *This is yogurt for children.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add buttermilk and stir until well mixed.
Begin to add flour, soda and salt mixture a little at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition. Add fruit and nuts; mix well.
Chill cookie mixture at least 1 hour.
(This dough can be refrigerated for up to 1 week before baking.)
Makes a delicious, chewy cookie.
Any candied fruit can be used in this recipe, but I prefer to use red and green cherries, pineapple and dates.

title: pumpkin swirls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan. Line top and sides with waxed paper and grease again.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients. Pour into pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes. Remove from oven; cool 1 to 2 minutes and dump on cotton cloth, dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll and let cool completely; unroll after cool and stuff with filling.
Reroll and refrigerate or freeze.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
While still hot poke holes all over cake and pour cream of coconut all over and let soak in a little, then pour Eagle Brand milk all over cake.
Let cake cool completely and put Cool Whip on top.
Then sprinkle coconut all over top.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking soda together three times.
Cream butter thoroughly, adding sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat well, then add chocolate. Blend.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add vanilla. Bake in a greased 8 x 8 x-2-inch pan in moderate oven (325°) for one hour.

title: rosy beef stroganoff
directions: Shake cut up round steak in a bag with 3 tablespoons flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Brown meat, onion and garlic salt in 2 tablespoons shortening in skillet.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients well in mixer.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken-broccoli cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken between 2 pieces of plastic wrap.
With meat mallet or rolling pin, pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness. Place a ham slice and cheese slice on each breast half.
Roll up chicken from narrow end, jelly roll fashion.
Secure with wooden toothpick.

title: california casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef with green pepper and onion until meat is browned and vegetables are tender; drain.
Add next 11 ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Add noodles; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, pork, veal, bread crumbs, parsley, salt, nutmeg, egg and milk in a large bowl.
Mix together well.
Shape mixture into balls, using 1 tablespoon for each.

title: heavenly pineapple cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat yolks and whites separately. Cream butter, sugar and beaten egg yolks.
Mix salt, flour and baking powder and sift together.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to butter mixture. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Divide mixture and place in 3 prepared cake pans.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Put together in bowl and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: head over heels pudding cake
directions: Mix the margarine, 3/4 cup sugar, milk, 2 2/3 tablespoons of cocoa, salt, flour, baking powder, Grape Nuts cereal and vanilla into a batter.
Mix together with a few ounces of water the 1/2 cup sugar, honey and 1/4 cup of cocoa.
Spoon over batter.
Bake in a casserole dish in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve from casserole, turning each serving into individual dessert bowl.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the water with a pinch of ginger added (it is extra good if you use the water used for boiling potatoes). Mix scalded milk, shortening, sugar and salt well.
Let cook to lukewarm (so as not to destroy the action of the yeast). Add yeast mixture and mix well. Add the flour and mix well.
Let set 10 minutes. Knead on a floured board until smooth and elastic.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups tomato juice with kraut juice.
Put in an ice tray and freeze.
Use remaining juice, onion, lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon salt; put in jar.
Cover and place in refrigerator. Before serving, set out tomato ice to melt a little.
Cut into small pieces.
Place in glass and cover with other juice.

title: frosted creams
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Spread on an oblong sheet pan (jelly roll pan).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Ice with confectioners sugar and water.
Ice while still warm.

title: meat loaf(dave's)
directions: Mix all items and salt and pepper to taste except last 3 items. Put in 13 x 9 pan 3/4 of the mixture.
Lay the cheese and top with remaining mixture, causing the cheese to be in a pocket.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with ketchup and sugar.
Bake another 15 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Bring soup bone to boil in 2 to 3 quarts water and add bouillon cubes.
Reduce heat and cook just above simmer for 2 hours.
Take out soup bone; cut off any meat and return to soup mixture.
Add tomato soup and add water.
Add potatoes, onion, green beans and corn.
Stir in celery seed, parsley and garlic. Bring to a boil, then cook for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Put nuts and coconut in bottom of pan. Mix cake per directions on box and pour on nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine. Mix with cream cheese until well blended.
Add sugar.
Beat about 2 minutes and pour on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cake will open at top as it cooks.

title: blueberry fruit salad
directions: Fructose is a sweetener that may be used by some diabetics. Please ask your doctor before using these recipes.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Cook in water until done.
While potatoes are hot, mash and chop boiled eggs.
Add the pickle relish, mayonnaise, mustard and onion.
Add salt, pepper and celery seed to taste.

title: crunchy nut cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in; add nuts.
Form into balls (1 level tablespoon).
Place on ungreased sheet.
Flatten with bottom of greased glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: billy sunday pudding
directions: Soak tapioca overnight in enough water to cover well. Put in large baking dish, then add brown sugar, dates and enough water to keep moist. Put in oven and bake, adding more water as needed to keep from being dry. Stir occasionally. When tapioca is clear and pudding is thick, remove. Add vanilla and nuts; cool. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: tomato crouton salad
directions: Preheat
oven
Toss bread cubes with 1 tablespoon olive
oil,
oregano,
salt and pepper.
Bake in single layer
for 20
minutes or until golden.
Cut cucumbers into 1 inch cubes. Combine with all other ingredients except arugula and
bread cubes.
Just
before
serving, add bread cubes and toss.
Divide arugula among 6 plates and top with salad.

title: noodle surprise
directions: Cook noodles and broccoli in pot of boiling water.
Strain noodles when done.
Add mushroom soup, mushrooms and ham.
Simmer until hot.
Any other ingredients can be added to liking.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook onion and squash until tender.
Combine all in a casserole bowl and top with cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: In a large pot, brown hamburger.
Drain fat and add onion. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add garlic, chopped tomatoes, black beans, corn, tomato sauce and taco mix.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Place soup in serving bowls over Fritos.
Top with cheese and sour cream.

title: spaghetti meat sauce, japanese style
directions: Brown ground meat; drain fat.
Set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a pan; stir-fry onion, ginger, garlic and carrot until onion is tender.
Add browned meat, then add ketchup, tomato juice, salt, Tonkatsu or teriyaki sauce, sugar and bay leaves. Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes; stir occasionally.
Add pepper to taste.
Serve over al dente spaghetti and Parmesan cheese.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread softened cheese on large platter.
Add other ingredients in given order.
Let stand several hours to mingle flavors.
Serve with corn chips.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in margarine until transparent. Add beef broth, bouillon, water
and wine.
Simmer.
Put croutons in bottom of soup bowls.
Fill with soup mix. Top with Swiss cheese and put in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: mom tom's butterscotch pudding chocolate pudding
directions: Mix together brown sugar, salt, flour, 1/2 cup milk and egg yolks.
Set aside.
Brown in heavy pan.
Add butter and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Slowly add brown sugar mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook unti thickens, then add vanilla.
Refrigerate after it has cooled.

title: jean sanders' pumpkin nut bread
directions: Mix first seven dry ingredients well, saving a little flour to sprinkle over nuts and raisins.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Into the well, add oil, eggs, water and pumpkin. Mix well, then add nuts and raisins.
Mix well and pour into 3 loaf pans or 6 small greased and floured pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: seafoam frosting
directions: Cook until soft ball is formed.
