Pour into egg whites and when fluffy, add vinegar.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients in 2 cups hot water. Add 2 cups cold water.
Freeze.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill one hour.
Great to put into hollowed Swedish rye bread.
Cut slice from top of bread.
Remove center, leaving 1-inch shell.
Cut or tear removed bread into bite size pieces.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together.
Store in tight jars.
Use 2 or 3 teaspoons mix in each cup of hot water.

title: oatmeal almond cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, margarine and corn syrup until fluffy.
Add egg whites and extract; mix well.
Gradually add combined remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by 1/4 measuring cup about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press into 3-inch circles.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes until golden brown.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add chili powder, salt, pepper, tomato soup, corn and 1 can liquid (juice from corn plus water to make 1 can).
Mix together and simmer about 15 minutes.
Pour mixture in a pan.
Mix cornbread mix as directed on box and pour into meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: mock potato salad(low-fat)
directions: Cook cauliflower about half done; dice.
Add one 14 ounce jar of pimento, diced.
Also dice celery and green pepper; add to the rest of the ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown
onions
and hamburger together.	Add Ragu, pizza sauce, oregano,
garlic
powder, salt and pepper;
simmer for approximately
1/2 hour.
Cook lasagne as directed on box.	In a 9 x	12-inch
or
a 12 x 12-inch pan, start with a layer of sauce, lasagne,
cottage
cheese
and
sharp cheese.
Repeat. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pasta salad
directions: Add rotini to salted, boiling water until tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over cooled rotini.
Chill and serve.
Keeps up to 1 week in the refrigerator.

title: yohos
directions: In a large frypan, heat oil.
Saute onion, garlic and green pepper until onion is transparent, about 5 minutes.
Add seasoned salt, cayenne pepper and water; bring to a slow boil.
Add tomato paste; stir until smooth.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add oysters.
Stir and let cook 5 minutes. Remove immediately from heat.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Beat butter in a large bowl at medium speed until fluffy. Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine flour, soda and salt; gradually add to butter mixture, beating until blended.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: crazy crust apple pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, egg, shortening and water.
Blend well; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into a 9-inch pie pan.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies for bottom layer.
Reserve 1/2 cup for garnish. Add margarine to crushed cookies and press in bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese and sugar; beat well.
Stir in 1/2 of Cool Whip. Spread on top of cookie crust and chill 30 minutes.

title: mex chops
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, brown chops in oil on one side.
Turn chops, add salsa and chilies.
Lower heat; cover and simmer gently for 8 to 10 minutes. Serves four.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix and pat into cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: tomatoes, kraut and kielbasa
directions: Cut up kielbasa and wash thoroughly.
Put kielbasa, kraut and honey in crock-pot.
Cook on low for about 4 hours.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Whip milk and pudding mix until thick.
Add sour cream.
Line pan and sides with vanilla wafers.
Next, put in pudding, bananas and Cool Whip alternately.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: mumu's chocolate pound cake
directions: Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in 10-inch greased, floured and lined tube pan.
Use wax paper, if needed.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar until creamy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.

title: strawberry-orange shake
directions: In food processor, pulse berries to chop. Add juice concentrate.
Puree.
Add milk and yogurt.
Blend.
Serves 6.

title: mom's cucumber salad
directions: Pare cucumbers; scoop out seeds.
Slice very thinly; using a grater works best.
Drain cucumbers in a colander for at least 2 hours (can drain overnight in refrigerator).
After cucumbers have drained, combine in bowl with onion, sour cream and mayonnaise. Mix thoroughly, adding sugar, salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put fruit in baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over fruit. Mix together remaining ingredients and spoon over fruit.
Cook at 325° until top is brown and firm.
Delicious served warm and topped with ice cream.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add beaten eggs.
Add baking soda dissolved in hot water.
Sift together flour and salt, and add to butter mixture.
Stir in nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheets and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 100 small or fewer large cookies.

title: broccoli cheddar meat loaf
directions: Finely roll 12 crackers.
Mix cracker crumbs, turkey, onions, 2 tablespoons chili sauce, parsley and egg.
On waxed paper, pat meat mixture into 12 x 6-inch rectangle.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Mash cream cheese until softened.
Chop beef into tiny pieces; lay on wax paper to dry more while preparing onions.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup dried beef.
Mix well and shape into a ball.
Coat and press remaining beef pieces on ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving. Eat with crackers of your choice.

title: caramel topping
directions: Mix together and serve with apple slices or pineapple slices.

title: bread and butter cake
directions: Mix in bowl the cream cheese alternately with powdered sugar and eggs.
Save a small amount of powdered sugar to sift on top. Add vanilla.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until the top is light brown.
Sift leftover powdered sugar on top.

title: fresh mint tea
directions: Place tea bags and mint leaves in a 3-quart pitcher.
Add the boiling water and steep until cool.
Discard tea bags and mint leaves.
Add orange and lemon juices, sugar and 6 cups of water to tea mixture, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Serve over ice and garnish with mint sprigs and orange slices.
Serving Size: 12.
Preparation Time: 0:30.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: In large baking dish, arrange chicken thighs.
Cover with a mixture of remaining ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken cortez
directions: Microwave chicken 16 to 18 minutes in a glass dish covered with wax paper.
Cool and tear into bite size pieces.
Combine chicken, sour cream, soup, milk, hot sauce, onion, celery, chiles, tortillas and cheese.
Blend well.
Microwave 12 to 14 minutes, turning halfway through the cooking time.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash and mushroom soup; place in a small baking dish. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add melted butter to dressing; cover the squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1/2 of cake in the bottom of punch bowl or extra large bowl.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Spread half of the other ingredients in layers in order given.
Crumble rest of cake and repeat with second half of ingredients in layers in order given. Garnish with cherries or strawberries and nuts.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Stir in nuts and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool and serve.

title: meringue
directions: In medium bowl, beat the egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar at medium speed about 1 minute or until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar about 1 tablespoon at a time, beating at high speed with mixer for about 4 minutes more or until soft glossy peaks and sugar is dissolved.
Spread immediately over pie carefully, sealing to edge of pastry to prevent shrinkage.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes to brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake 350° for one hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix melted butter with cracker crumbs. Set aside.
Mix soup, sour cream and poppy seed together.
Layer the cooked chicken, soup mixture and cracker crumbs in an 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with the cracker crumbs.
Bake until hot and bubbly, about 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cheese straws
directions: Let cheese soften.
Mix cheese, flour, pepper, salt and butter.
Mix and knead until soft and creamy.
Cook at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
If there is a tendency to spread, just add flour.

title: southwestern chicken
directions: Combine tomatoes, salsa, onion, garlic and salt.
Set aside. Coat chicken with flour.
In 10-inch skillet with lid, heat oil on medium heat.
Saute chicken 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until golden.
Pour sauce over, cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until tender.
Serve on rice with a dollop of sour cream.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip cupcakes(makes 18 or 19)
directions: Cream together sugar, cream cheese and add salt and egg.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: pa. dutch green beans
directions: In a skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Drain off all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add onion and brown lightly.
Stir in cornstarch, salt and dry mustard.
Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Add this to skillet.
Cook, stirring until mixture boils. Blend in brown sugar and vinegar.
Add green beans and beat thoroughly.
Turn into serving dish and garnish with egg and crumbled bacon.
Serves 4.

title: petite caramel pecan rolls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar, margarine and corn syrup.
Blend well.
Spread in bottom of ungreased 8 or 9-inch round cake pan.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over rectangles evenly. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of the pecans on each rectangle.
Starting at shorter side, roll up each rectangle; pinch edges to seal.
Cut each roll into 4 pieces.
Place, cut side down, over brown sugar mixture in pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 27 minutes until golden brown.
Cool in pan for 1 minute.
Makes 16 rolls.

title: oven rich potatoes
directions: Bake and split potatoes.
Scoop into flat baking dish.
Add soft butter, salt and pepper.
Cream mixture together.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: kix cereal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Mix sugars, peanut butter, butter, shortening, egg, baking soda and baking powder in 4-quart bowl thoroughly. Stir in cereal and chocolate chips. Shape dough slightly by rounded tablespoonfuls; place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake until golden, 10 to 12 minutes. Cool 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies. May substitute butterscotch chips for the chocolate chips.

title: biscuit mix
directions: In large mixing bowl, sift together baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Store in covered container up to 6 weeks at room temperature.
For longer storage, freeze.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix ingredients in blender on high for 1 minute. Add 4 or 5 ice cubes. Blend until ice is crushed.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Toss vegetables and cheese together.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over vegetables and cheese; mix well.
Cover and store in the refrigerator.
Serves 8.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease black (iron) skillet.
Mix all ingredients and pour into skillet.
Bake until golden brown.

title: french coutou
directions: In a covered pan, cook 2 to 3 hours on low heat; water will be totally absorbed when done.
Add up to 4 teaspoons each of cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and allspice.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix together and pour into hot milk.
When serving, add marshmallows.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Slice potatoes thinly.
Cook in salted water until tender. Drain.
Melt margarine over low heat; stir in flour and milk. Cook slowly until slightly thickened.
In casserole dish, layer potatoes, ham, cheese and milk mixture, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
May also be cooked on High in microwave for 5 minutes.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use ungreased cookie sheets.
Blend cake mix, oil, water and eggs.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute.
Then remove to rack to finish cooling.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large skillet, slowly cook onions in butter until lightly browned, about 25 minutes.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 cup boiling water.
Combine bouillon, 2 quarts water, white wine and onions in large kettle.
Cover and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Near end of cooking time, add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to soup.
Put a thin slice of French bread in soup bowl.
Add soup and top with shredded cheese.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour half of batter into baking dish.
Add cheese.
Top cheese with peppers.
Add remaining batter.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Cook sweet potatoes and peel when cool.
Preheat oven to 325°. In a large bowl, beat sweet potatoes, butter, milk or orange juice and pepper until smooth.
Spoon mixture into casserole; top with as much drained, crushed pineapple as you wish, and sprinkle as much brown sugar on top as you wish.
Bake 45 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion lightly.
Add other ingredients, stirring after each addition.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.

title: pastry bows
directions: Work all above ingredients together.
Knead well for 5 to 10 minutes.
Flour table and divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll out to a thin layer.
Cut into 2-inch strips and again to 2-inch lengths. Slit again down center of each diagonal pastry.
Now bring one corner through center slit.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Take okra and puree until it becomes a "gob of green gue."
Set aside.
In an iron skillet, use the 1/2 cup bacon grease to brown 1 cup plain flour, using low to medium heat and stirring often, until it turns to dark caramel color, usually about 45 minutes.
Turn off heat and add okra.

Saute onions, peppers, celery and garlic in 1 1/2 sticks of margarine until completely cooked, then add this to the other ingredients and the roux and continue to cook as desired. Add seafood as desired just an hour before ready to serve.

title: pride of iowa cookies
directions: Blend sugars and shortening.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Stir in vanilla, coconut, oats and nuts.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with the bottom of a glass.
Bake in 375° oven until light brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; cool.
Peel and grate.
Put in well-buttered, oblong casserole dish.
Heat together remaining ingredients, except paprika, and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Don't overbake as it dries out.

title: kim's mexican rice
directions: Simmer rice in 4 cups of water for 20 minutes in covered saucepan; do not stir or remove lid or rice will get sticky.
In a large pan, saute the onion in oil until tender.
Turn heat off and add soup, sour cream, green chiles and 2 cups of the cheese.
When rice is done, stir it into this mixture.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan and top with remaining cheese.
(You can top with black olives, if desired, or add some chopped chicken breast.)
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: codfish finger cakes(bolinnos de bacalhau)
directions: Soak codfish in water for 24 hours (replacing water 3 or 4 times).
Cook in fresh water for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Debone and shred codfish by hand; mince with a fork or in food processor. Add mashed potatoes to codfish, along with onion and parsley; mix well.
Add beaten eggs, salt and pepper; stir together.
With floured hands, form cakes into the shape of a small egg.
Fry in 1/2 inch boiling oil or margarine until golden brown in color. Drain on paper towels.
Garnish with parsley and sliced tomato wedges.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer cubed bread.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard together and pour over bread.
Crumble the sausage over this.
Sprinkle the cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pork chops 'n potato bake
directions: Brown chops in lightly greased skillet. Sprinkle with salt; set aside. Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Arrange chops over the potatoes. Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: creole cauliflower
directions: Saute cauliflower, onion, bell pepper and celery.
Mix vegetables with tomatoes, mushroom soup, salt and pepper to taste. Cook until thick.
Place in 12-inch casserole.
Cover with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown and cheese is melted.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine in medium bowl the shrimp, mayonnaise, cheese, onion, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Chill at least 1 hour. Serve with crackers.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: mud pie dessert
directions: Combine crushed cookies with 1/3 c. melted butter.
Press into a 13X9-inch pan.
Spread with softened ice cream, cover and freeze.

title: one dish dinner
directions: Brown meat. Add all ingredients. Steam for 30 minutes. Uncover and cook for 30 minutes or until macaroni is done.
Stir occasionally. Serve with green salad.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine sugar, water and coffee; simmer 1 hour.
Chill 1 hour. Add vodka and vanilla.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break prepared angel food cake into chunks and spread into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or 3-quart dish.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup cornstarch and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add 1 1/2 cups water and cook on low until thick, stirring constantly.
When ready, put some hot mix into 3 egg yolks and stir well.
Pour back into hot mix, stir and cook a few minutes.
Take off and add 1/4 cup lemon juice and 1/3 stick margarine.
Mix well.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: chili
directions: Combine ground beef, tomato sauce, green pepper, onion, water, chili powder, salt and sugar; simmer 1 hour.
Add beans.
Mix oil and flour together and add to beans.
Mix all ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: rosemary's macaroni and cheese
directions: Fill a 2-quart pan half full of water.
Add salt (to make it boil).
When water boils, add macaroni.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes until the water is almost gone.
Do not drain.
Cheese sauce (in different pan):
Place small amount of milk in pan; stir in dry mustard until dissolved.
Add cheese and rest of milk.
Place on low heat; stir often until cheese and butter have melted.
Add to cooked macaroni.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries and lemon juice. Then stir the mixture until it is soft and leave it in the refrigerator until partially set.	Mix cream cheese powdered sugar, salt and vanilla.
Gradually blend 12 oz. frozen whipped topping, thawed.
Spread half of this over graham cracker crust. Then 1/2 of raspberries. Alternate. Chill and serve.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken chunks in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream (can add milk if wanted).
Heat in microwave to blend.
Pour over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix in poppy seed.
Add cracker mixture as a topping to chicken casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add creamed sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add pumpkin and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: baked sliced eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant crosswise into 8 (1/2-inch) slices and peel. Brush each slice with melted butter.
Add remaining butter, salt and pepper to bread crumbs.
Dip slices into buttered crumbs. Bake, uncovered, on a baking sheet in a 450° oven for 18 minutes. Serves 4.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Stir in tomato paste, onion and seasonings.
Cook on low heat for 5 minutes; stir often.
Place biscuits in greased muffin tin; cover bottom and sides.
Spoon 1/4 cup mixture into cups and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400°. These are good reheated in microwave.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve packages of Jell-O in boiling water and pickle juice. Cool until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat sweetened milk, egg and vanilla. Stir in chips and pecans.
Spread evenly over crust.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Makes 36 bars.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Saute chicken in oil until lightly browned; remove to platter. Saute onions and garlic until tender.
Add tomatoes; cook until tomatoes are mushy.
Return chicken to skillet.
Add wine; cook until chicken is cooked through.
Add mushrooms; cook just until mushrooms are tender.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine jello and pineapple (with juice), then heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat and cool completely.
Add buttermilk and refrigerate until it starts to gel, then add Cool Whip and pecans.
Return to refrigerator.
Use 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine egg, salt and milk.
Add enough flour to make dough stiff.
Roll very thin.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Roll up and slice 1/8-inch thick.
Let dry for 2 hours.
Drop in boiling water or broth and cook 10 minutes.

title: spanish eggplant
directions: Boil eggplant and onion until very tender.
Drain and mash. Place in greased baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sift the flour with sugar, salt and cinnamon.

Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse corn meal (a pastry blender works best). Arrange evenly over peaches. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm with ice cream or cream. (Apples also work well in place of the peaches.)

title: frozen salad
directions: Whip cream cheese until smooth and creamy.
Add sour cream; mix.
Add remaining ingredients; mix and freeze.

title: quick rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and about 1/2 the flour.
Beat thoroughly 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat in remaining flour gradually until smooth.
Let rise 30 minutes in a warm place.
Stir down batter and drop into greased medium muffin pans.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Bake 10 minutes in 425° oven.
Makes 1 dozen rolls.

title: hot ham and cheese
directions: Slice rolls in half lengthwise.
Spread mustard mixture on both sides of rolls.
Layer ham and cheese and put top part of rolls on ham layer.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake on 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: savannah dirt cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar. Prepare pudding according to directions.
Once set, add to cream cheese mixture and blend thoroughly.
Crush Oreos and line bottom of dish.
Spoon in cream cheese mixture and alternate cookies and mixture until dish is full.
Finish with a layer of cookies.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook in crock-pot on low heat around 10 to 12 hours.
Drain liquid.
Chop up meat for excellent sandwiches.

title: bergen fish soup(bergens fiskesuppe)
directions: Add carrots, parsnips and fish to soup stock.
Bring to boil and reduce to simmer 10 minutes.
Add leeks and simmer 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and lift out fish; set aside on platter.
Beat egg yolks in bowl and add 1/2 cup hot soup 1 tablespoon at a time.
Pour this back into soup in thin stream, beating continuously with a wire whisk.
Separate fish into flakes and add to soup.
Season with salt and pepper and reheat.
Ladle into bowls and sprinkle with parsley and 1 tablespoon sour cream.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; remove stems.
Cut half the stems into little pieces (I use my Oscar).
Mix bread crumbs, Swiss cheese, butter, onions and salt.
Stuff mushrooms.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes and enjoy! Yields 24 appetizers.

title: turtle cookies
directions: You will also need a waffle iron.

title: prune pudding
directions: Blend all dry ingredients together.
Add to them alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts, prunes, oil and vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Cut loose from sides of pan and cut in squares (in pan).
Pour icing over it.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on box.
Brown beef and onions in oil and drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until slightly thickened.

title: brownies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make pastry combining flour, baking powder, salt and shortening.
Add milk and egg.
Roll out as pie crust.
Prepare apples by peeling and coring them.
Wrap pastry around each apple, pinching edges together.
Combine water, sugar and butter and bring to a boil.
Pour syrup into baking dish and place dumplings in hot syrup.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°, then 45 minutes at 275°.

title: chicken in rice casserole
directions: Boil water and add soup mix.
Brown onion, celery and pepper. Add rice, chicken and remaining ingredients to soup mixture and stir.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 15.

title: mama's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix and jello.
Add oil and milk.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each.
Stir in frozen strawberries, coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: fiesta beet salad
directions: Add 1 cup hot water to gelatin in a mixing bowl and stir until dissolved, then add remaining ingredients and stir together.
Pour into square pan or mold and chill until firm.

title: lazy pie
directions: Melt oleo in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Beat remaining ingredients together until smooth.
Pour in dish with oleo.
Dump pie filling over mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas snowballs
directions: Soften cream cheese with extract.
Mix in sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, and stir in 2 cups coconut.
Butter hands and roll dough into 1-inch balls, then roll in 1/2 cup coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: beef shish-kebab
directions: Place cubed meat in bowl; combine remaining ingredients.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine soup, vegetables, chicken, milk, thyme and black pepper.
Spoon into crust.
Cover with your other crust and cut slits in it.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: blueberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
When cooled, add the pineapple and pie filling.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Spread with whipped cream topping.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Serves 15.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve as a dip for apple slices.

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Beat eggs; stir in water.
Add biscuit mix, mixing until smooth.
Stir in 1 cup cheese and mustard.
Spoon batter into lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 9 servings.

title: apple bread
directions: Blend together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Blend together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add apples, milk, vanilla and nuts. Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pan; sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini in dill sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine zucchini, onion, water, salt, bouillon granules and dill weed.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Add butter, sugar and lemon juice.
Remove from heat.
Blend flour into sour cream; add to zucchini mixture and return to heat.
Stir and cook until thickened and bubbly.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter, add sugars and blend well. Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and stir until there are no lumps; add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into a long 1 1/2 to 2-inch deep pan, sprayed with cooking spray.
Cook approximately 30 minutes.
Do not use electric mixer.

title: delicious pork chops
directions: Arrange chops in a single layer in baking dish.
Combine next five ingredients in a bowl.
Spread half the mixture over chops.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Place apples in sheet pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over them. Add sliced margarine and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Spread on pizza size pan.
Pour sauce over and spread.
Sprinkle can of crabmeat over top.
Serve with crackers.

title: popcorn macaroons
directions: Chop popcorn finely and mix with nuts.
Beat egg whites in a separate bowl until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until egg whites form soft peaks.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Fold popcorn and nut mixture into egg whites.
Drop by half teaspoons onto lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Transfer to cooling rack immediately.
Each cookie contains approximately 20 calories.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, coconut and margarine in shallow pan and stir over medium heat.
After mixture reaches a boil, cook 2 minutes.
Take off heat and add the oatmeal, vanilla and the nuts. Stir about 2 minutes.
Drop from spoon onto foil.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Grease loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes after baking to settle.
Makes 2 loaves.
Loaves may be frozen and saved or given as gifts.
Serve sliced cold or warm.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Put in shallow baking dish.

title: exotic celery
directions: Cook celery 8 minutes and drain.
Put in a casserole, in order given, and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with crackers or any kind of crumbs.
Serves 12.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Melt butter. Add the rest of ingredients. Mix all together. Roll out and cut cookies. Put on a greased pan. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Cook rice.
Mix together the soup and sour cream.
Cut the ham into small chunks and add to soup mixture.
Stir in vegetables and rice.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish and add bread crumbs on top if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: one pot chicken dish
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Brown chicken on all sides. Then add onion and bell pepper.
Cook for a few minutes (4 to 5) until onion and bell pepper are soft.
Next add the ham, rice and chicken broth.
Add enough water to cover the rice.
Cover and cook over low-medium heat for about 45 minutes.
Stir the mixture often.
More water may need to be added to keep the rice from sticking.

title: cashew gravy
directions: Blend in blender until smooth and heat through.

title: hot punch drink
directions: Place spices in cheesecloth. Combine remaining ingredients in crock-pot. Put on No. 5 setting for 2 hours, then turn down to No. 2 setting. Keep warm for serving. Makes 24 (4 ounce) servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender and season with salt and pepper.
Add other vegetables, soup and sour cream.
Mix stuffing and melted margarine.
Line casserole dish with this mixture, leaving enough to cover top.
Pour squash mixture over stuffing and cover this with crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pecans in butter and bake 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Melt candy and put pecans in.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: *grace snapp's coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 2 minutes after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add coconut and flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Use a glaze as a topping.

title: seafood newburg deluxe
directions: Make a cream sauce with the butter, flour and cream.
Add salt, pepper and sherry.
Remove and add crabmeat, shrimp and mushrooms.
Pour into a buttered casserole or individual baking dishes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes, until cheese melts and sauce is bubbly.
Do not overcook.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: In medium bowl combine meat, egg, bread crumbs, garlic, onion and seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Shape in 24 bite-size meat balls. In 2-quart casserole, combine jelly, chili sauce and mustard.
Mix until well blended.
Add meat balls.
Cover with glass lid.
Heat at High 6 minutes and Medium-low 9 minutes.
Stir twice.
To complete, stir and let stand, uncovered, 3 minutes before serving.

title: marinated springs
directions: Blend together sugar, soup, vinegar and oil.
Toss all ingredients together and marinate at least 12 hours before serving.

title: pasta ala pesto
directions: In a covered blender, blend on high speed, olive oil, garlic and basil.
Let stand 15 minutes to allow flavors to mingle.

title: sweet broccoli slaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Pour over broccoli slaw mix, stirring gently.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with a slotted spoon.

title: chicken in a skillet with tomatoes
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and brown chicken; drain.
Add tomatoes and soup mix blended with water and reserved liquid. Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt and soda and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Cookies should still be puffy and just barely golden when removed from the oven.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Peel eggplant and cube; cook eggplant and onion in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Beat egg; blend in flour, eggplant and salt.
Drop by teaspoon in hot oil, turning to brown.

title: mexican pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a pie plate.
Prepare mashed potatoes as directed on package for 4 servings, except decrease water to 1 cup and omit the milk.
Stir in egg and green onions. Spread and press potato mixture evenly against bottom and side of pie plate.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.
Cook ground beef and chopped onion in skillet, stirring occasionally until beef is done; drain thoroughly.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into shell; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 2 or 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Garnish with sour cream, green bell peppers, tomatoes and avocado, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix
as
listed;
bake	in
greased and floured 2 quart baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stir-fry vegetables with chicken
directions: Stir-fry all vegetables until tender-crisp in small amount of oil.
Add chicken, sunflower seeds and water chestnuts, sliced. Season with soy sauce. Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.

title: cashew chicken-licken
directions: Bring to a boil the 2 cups water and salt.
Add rice and let water return to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer and cook 14 minutes. Meanwhile, saute diced onion, celery, and green pepper in fat until tender.
Combine sauteed vegetables with cooked rice.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Place in a greased 2-quart capacity baking dish.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 20-30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry cream squares
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, stirring occasionally until strawberries are thawed.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of mixture into an 8 x 8 x 12-inch pan.
Chill.
When firm, spread evenly with sour cream. Pour remaining gelatin mixture on top.
Chill until firm, then cut into 9 inch squares and top with sour cream.

title: old fashioned sour cream drops
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Add sour cream and vanilla, then mix.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt, then add to first mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and mash.
Mix with dry Italian dressing mix and sour cream.
Chill.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Take off heat and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Put spoonfuls on a sheet of wax paper.
Let cool.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sift together the flour and baking powder onto waxed paper.
Combine 1 cup of sugar and the rhubarb in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is completely melted and rhubarb begins to soften, 5 to 8 minutes.
Scrape into prepared baking pan, spreading evenly.

title: favorite molasses cookies
directions: Cream together the ingredients.
Roll in balls and roll in regular sugar before baking.
Bake at 345° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: summer sausage
directions: Shape into 4 logs and place on a rack inside a cookie sheet. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Take the foil off and leave the logs on the rack in the cookie sheet to take.

title: carrot-pineapple cake(delicious anytime)
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Combine dry ingredients and gradually blend into cream mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 or 9 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)
Cookies will be soft.
They will puff during baking and flatten upon cooling.
Cool on a cookie sheet until set, about 1 minute.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: crawfish etoufee
directions: Melt butter in pot; stir until light brown.
Add mix, stir over low heat until medium brown.
Add water, Ro-Tel and crawfish tails; cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook 15 minutes. Turn off heat and let stand for 15 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Eat and enjoy.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together a day ahead of time.
Delicious dip for celery, cauliflower, carrots, peppers, cucumber, etc.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand for 1 hour. Refrigerate until serving time.
Serves 10.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side down, in shallow baking dish.
Drain pineapple, measure 1/2 cup syrup.
Add to Basic Barbecue Sauce in a saucepan.
Stir in salt, ginger and soy sauce.
Blend cornstarch with tablespoon pineapple syrup or water; blend with sauce.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Brush chicken with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, brushing occasionally, with sauce and turn once after 30 minutes.
Add pineapple, green pepper, oranges and cherries to remaining sauce.
Heat and pour over chicken the last 5 minutes of baking time.

title: sweet bubble bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Drop frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with dry pudding and brown sugar.
Pour melted margarine over rolls and top with nuts.
Let stand for rolls to rise until double in size. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Dump out on large plates and enjoy.

title: lemon yummies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add egg, lemon rind and juice.
Mix well.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix. Form into rolls 1-inch in diameter.
Wrap and chill in refrigerator for approximately 4 to 6 hours.
Slice and place on baking sheet. Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 54 small cookies.

title: half moon cookies sumboosic
directions: Mix flour, butter, oil, mahlab, cinnamon, salt, anise seed and baking powder.
Add enough milk to blend together well.
Knead for several minutes until dough is soft and elastic.
Make dough into walnut size balls.
Roll dough into circles.
Place about a teaspoon of filling (ground walnuts, sugar and mahlab) into each circle.
Fold over the half moon shape and seal the edge by pressing with a fork.
Place on a cookie sheet about 1/4 inch apart and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until light brown and let cool.
Dip in syrup and drain in colander.
This can also be prepared by sprinkling hot sumboosic with confectioners sugar.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Boil to syrup the sugar, vinegar and water.
Cool and beat in egg, salt and pepper.
Mix cheese and mixture together and then add 1 jar cut up pimentos.

title: chicken enchilada casserole(or turkey)
directions: Mix sour cream, soups and green chilies to make the sauce.
On a tortilla layer about 1 tablespoon meat; sprinkle on about 1 teaspoon onion.
Add 1 tablespoon sauce.
Top with 1 tablespoon cheese.
Roll up tortilla and place seam side down in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Repeat until the baking dish is full.
Top with the remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger, pepperoni and onion together.
Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Place 1 to 2 tablespoons of mixture on each top or bottom of hamburger bun.
Bake open-faced for 10 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until smooth. Serves 2.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Do not double this recipe!!
Grease cookie sheet with margarine.
Stir together in bowl sugar and syrup.
Microwave 4 minutes on High; add peanuts.
Microwave 4 more minutes.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Stir.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Stir thoroughly. Pour quickly onto buttered cookie sheet and smooth out.

title: low calorie orange cake
directions: Stir 2 teaspoons sweetener into butter.
Add eggs; mix well. Add flour, salt and baking powder alternately with 1/3 cup orange juice, mixing until blended.
Pour into a 9-inch layer cake pan lined on the bottom with waxed paper.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (375°) for about 30 minutes (cake layer will be thin). Remove to serving plate and peel off paper.
Just before serving, mix remaining 1/2 teaspoon sweetener and 1/3 cup orange juice in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 2 to 3 minutes. Spoon over slightly warm or cold cake.
Makes 8 servings.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Shred up lettuce to line bottom of salad bowl (large bowl). Cut up pepper, onion and cucumber and put over lettuce.
Pour bacon bits and cheese over.
Layer with mayonnaise.
Keep layering with ingredients and putting mayonnaise over each layer until you get to top of bowl.
